var book = {
	"name": "Deuteronomy",
	"numChapters": 34,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>These are the words that Moses spoke to all Israel beyond the Jordan in the wilderness, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4894A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4894A\"></sup>the Arabah opposite <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4894B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4894B\"></sup>Suph, between <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4894C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4894C\"></sup>Paran and Tophel, Laban, Hazeroth, and Dizahab.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It is eleven days' journey from Horeb by the way of Mount Seir to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4895D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4895D\"></sup>Kadesh-barnea.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4896E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4896E\"></sup>In the fortieth year, on the first day of the eleventh month, Moses spoke to the people of Israel according to all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given him in commandment to them,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4897F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4897F\"></sup>he had defeated Sihon the king of the Amorites, who lived in Heshbon, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4897G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4897G\"></sup>Og the king of Bashan, who lived in Ashtaroth and in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4897H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4897H\"></sup>Edrei.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Beyond the Jordan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4898I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4898I\"></sup>in the land of Moab, Moses undertook to explain this law, saying,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God said to us in Horeb, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4899J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4899J\"></sup>‘You have stayed long enough at this mountain.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Turn and take your journey, and go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4900K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4900K\"></sup>the hill country of the Amorites and to all their neighbors in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4900L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4900L\"></sup>the Arabah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4900M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4900M\"></sup>in the hill country and in the lowland and in the Negeb and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4900N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4900N\"></sup>by the seacoast, the land of the Canaanites, and Lebanon, as far as the great river, the river Euphrates.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>See, I have set the land before you. Go in and take possession of the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to your fathers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4901O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4901O\"></sup>to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, to give to them and to their offspring after them.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“At that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4902P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4902P\"></sup>I said to you, ‘I am not able to bear you by myself.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has multiplied you, and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4903Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4903Q\"></sup>you are today as numerous as the stars of heaven.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4904R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4904R\"></sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, make you a thousand times as many as you are and bless you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4904S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4904S\"></sup>as he has promised you!",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4905T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4905T\"></sup>How can I bear by myself the weight and burden of you and your strife?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4906U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4906U\"></sup>Choose for your tribes wise, understanding, and experienced men, and I will appoint them as your heads.’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And you answered me, ‘The thing that you have spoken is good for us to do.’",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So I took the heads of your tribes, wise and experienced men, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4908V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4908V\"></sup>and set them as heads over you, commanders of thousands, commanders of hundreds, commanders of fifties, commanders of tens, and officers, throughout your tribes.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And I charged your judges at that time, ‘Hear the cases between your brothers, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4909W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4909W\"></sup>judge righteously between a man and his brother or the alien who is with him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4910X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4910X\"></sup>You shall not be partial in judgment. You shall hear the small and the great alike. You shall not be intimidated by anyone, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4910Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4910Y\"></sup>the judgment is God's. And the case that is too hard for you, you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4910Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4910Z\"></sup>bring to me, and I will hear it.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And I commanded you at that time all the things that you should do.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Then we set out from Horeb and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4912AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4912AA\"></sup>went through all that great and terrifying wilderness that you saw, on the way to the hill country of the Amorites, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God commanded us. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4912AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4912AB\"></sup>we came to Kadesh-barnea.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And I said to you, ‘You have come to the hill country of the Amorites, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God is giving us.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>See, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has set the land before you. Go up, take possession, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, has told you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4914AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4914AC\"></sup>Do not fear or be dismayed.’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then all of you came near me and said, ‘Let us send men before us, that they may explore the land for us and bring us word again of the way by which we must go up and the cities into which we shall come.’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The thing seemed good to me, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4916AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4916AD\"></sup>I took twelve men from you, one man from each tribe.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4917AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4917AE\"></sup>they turned and went up into the hill country, and came to the Valley of Eshcol and spied it out.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And they took in their hands some of the fruit of the land and brought it down to us, and brought us word again and said, ‘It is a good land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God is giving us.’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“Yet you would not go up, but rebelled against the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4920AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4920AF\"></sup>you murmured in your tents and said, ‘Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4920AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4920AG\"></sup>hated us he has brought us out of the land of Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4920AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4920AH\"></sup>to give us into the hand of the Amorites, to destroy us.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Where are we going up? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4921AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4921AI\"></sup>Our brothers have made our hearts melt, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4921AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4921AJ\"></sup>“The people are greater and taller than we. The cities are great and fortified up to heaven. And besides, we have seen <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4921AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4921AK\"></sup>the sons of the Anakim there.”’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then I said to you, ‘Do not be in dread or afraid of them.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God who goes before you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4923AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4923AL\"></sup>will himself fight for you, just as he did for you in Egypt before your eyes,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and in the wilderness, where you have seen how the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4924AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4924AM\"></sup>carried you, as a man carries his son, all the way that you went until you came to this place.’",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Yet in spite of this word <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4925AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4925AN\"></sup>you did not believe the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4926AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4926AO\"></sup>who went before you in the way <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4926AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4926AP\"></sup>to seek you out a place to pitch your tents, in fire by night and in the cloud by day, to show you by what way you should go.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard your words and was angered, and he swore,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4928AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4928AQ\"></sup>‘Not one of these men of this evil generation shall see the good land that I swore to give to your fathers,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4929AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4929AR\"></sup>except Caleb the son of Jephunneh. He shall see it, and to him and to his children I will give the land on which he has trodden, because he has wholly followed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!’",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Even with me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4930AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4930AS\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was angry on your account and said, ‘You also shall not go in there.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4931AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4931AT\"></sup>Joshua the son of Nun, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4931AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4931AU\"></sup>who stands before you, he shall enter. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4931AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4931AV\"></sup>Encourage him, for he shall cause Israel to inherit it.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And as for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4932AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4932AW\"></sup>your little ones, who you said would become a prey, and your children, who today <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4932AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4932AX\"></sup>have no knowledge of good or evil, they shall go in there. And to them I will give it, and they shall possess it.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>But as for you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4933AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4933AY\"></sup>turn, and journey into the wilderness in the direction of the Red Sea.’",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“Then you answered me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4934AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4934AZ\"></sup>‘We have sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. We ourselves will go up and fight, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God commanded us.’ And every one of you fastened on his weapons of war and thought it easy to go up into the hill country.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4935BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4935BA\"></sup>‘Say to them, Do not go up or fight, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4935BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4935BB\"></sup>for I am not in your midst, lest you be defeated before your enemies.’",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>So I spoke to you, and you would not listen; but you rebelled against the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4936BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4936BC\"></sup>presumptuously went up into the hill country.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4937BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4937BD\"></sup>Then the Amorites who lived in that hill country came out against you and chased you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4937BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4937BE\"></sup>as bees do and beat you down in Seir as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4937BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4937BF\"></sup>Hormah.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>And you returned and wept before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not listen to your voice or give ear to you.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4939BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4939BG\"></sup>you remained at Kadesh many days, the days that you remained there."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>“Then we turned and journeyed into the wilderness in the direction of the Red Sea, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4940A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4940A\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> told me. And for many days we traveled around Mount Seir.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>‘You have been traveling around this mountain country <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4942B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4942B\"></sup>long enough. Turn northward",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and command the people, “You are about to pass through the territory of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4943C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4943C\"></sup>your brothers, the people of Esau, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4943D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4943D\"></sup>who live in Seir; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4943E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4943E\"></sup>they will be afraid of you. So be very careful.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Do not contend with them, for I will not give you any of their land, no, not so much as for the sole of the foot to tread on, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4944F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4944F\"></sup>I have given Mount Seir to Esau as a possession.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4945G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4945G\"></sup>You shall purchase food from them with money, that you may eat, and you shall also buy water from them with money, that you may drink.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has blessed you in all the work of your hands. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4946H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4946H\"></sup>He knows your going through this great wilderness. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4946I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4946I\"></sup>These forty years the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has been with you. You have lacked nothing.”’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4947J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4947J\"></sup>we went on, away from our brothers, the people of Esau, who live in Seir, away from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4947K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4947K\"></sup>the Arabah road from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4947L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4947L\"></sup>Elath and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4947M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4947M\"></sup>Ezion-geber.“And we turned and went in the direction of the wilderness of Moab.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4948N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4948N\"></sup>‘Do not harass Moab or contend with them in battle, for I will not give you any of their land for a possession, because I have given <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4948O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4948O\"></sup>Ar to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4948P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4948P\"></sup>the people of Lot for a possession.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>(<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4949Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4949Q\"></sup>The Emim formerly lived there, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4949R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4949R\"></sup>a people great and many, and tall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4949S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4949S\"></sup>as the Anakim.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Like the Anakim they are also counted as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4950T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4950T\"></sup>Rephaim, but the Moabites call them Emim.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4951U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4951U\"></sup>The Horites also lived in Seir formerly, but the people of Esau dispossessed them and destroyed them from before them and settled in their place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4951V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4951V\"></sup>as Israel did to the land of their possession, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave to them.)",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>‘Now rise up and go over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4952W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4952W\"></sup>the brook Zered.’ So we went over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4952X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4952X\"></sup>the brook Zered.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And the time from our leaving <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4953Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4953Y\"></sup>Kadesh-barnea until we crossed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4953Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4953Z\"></sup>the brook Zered was thirty-eight years, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4953AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4953AA\"></sup>until the entire generation, that is, the men of war, had perished from the camp, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had sworn to them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For indeed the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was against them, to destroy them from the camp, until they had perished.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“So as soon as all the men of war had perished and were dead from among the people,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>‘Today you are to cross the border of Moab at Ar.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And when you approach the territory of the people of Ammon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4958AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4958AB\"></sup>do not harass them or contend with them, for I will not give you any of the land of the people of Ammon as a possession, because I have given it to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4958AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4958AC\"></sup>the sons of Lot for a possession.’",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>(It is also counted as a land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4959AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4959AD\"></sup>Rephaim. Rephaim formerly lived there—but the Ammonites call them Zamzummim—",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4960AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4960AE\"></sup>a people great and many, and tall as the Anakim; but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> destroyed them before the Ammonites, and they dispossessed them and settled in their place,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>as he did for the people of Esau, who live in Seir, when he destroyed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4961AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4961AF\"></sup>the Horites before them and they dispossessed them and settled in their place even to this day.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>As for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4962AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4962AG\"></sup>the Avvim, who lived in villages as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4962AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4962AH\"></sup>Gaza, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4962AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4962AI\"></sup>the Caphtorim, who came from Caphtor, destroyed them and settled in their place.)",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>‘Rise up, set out on your journey and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4963AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4963AJ\"></sup>go over the Valley of the Arnon. Behold, I have given into your hand Sihon the Amorite, king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4963AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4963AK\"></sup>Heshbon, and his land. Begin to take possession, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4963AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4963AL\"></sup>contend with him in battle.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>This day I will begin to put <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4964AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4964AM\"></sup>the dread and fear of you on the peoples who are under the whole heaven, who shall hear the report of you and shall tremble and be in anguish because of you.’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“So I sent messengers from the wilderness of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4965AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4965AN\"></sup>Kedemoth to Sihon the king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4965AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4965AO\"></sup>Heshbon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4965AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4965AP\"></sup>with words of peace, saying,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4966AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4966AQ\"></sup>‘Let me pass through your land. I will go only by the road; I will turn aside neither to the right nor to the left.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4967AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4967AR\"></sup>You shall sell me food for money, that I may eat, and give me water for money, that I may drink. Only let me pass through on foot,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4968AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4968AS\"></sup>as the sons of Esau who live in Seir and the Moabites who live in Ar did for me, until I go over the Jordan into the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God is giving to us.’",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4969AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4969AT\"></sup>Sihon the king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4969AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4969AU\"></sup>Heshbon would not let us pass by him, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4969AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4969AV\"></sup>hardened his spirit and made his heart obstinate, that he might give him into your hand, as he is this day.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘Behold, I have begun to give Sihon and his land over to you. Begin to take possession, that you may occupy his land.’",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4971AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4971AW\"></sup>Sihon came out against us, he and all his people, to battle at Jahaz.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4972AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4972AX\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God gave him over to us, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4972AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4972AY\"></sup>we defeated him and his sons and all his people.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And we captured all his cities at that time and devoted to destruction every <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4973AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4973AZ\"></sup>city, men, women, and children. We left no survivors.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Only the livestock we took as spoil for ourselves, with the plunder of the cities that we captured.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4975BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4975BA\"></sup>From Aroer, which is on the edge of the Valley of the Arnon, and from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4975BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4975BB\"></sup>the city that is in the valley, as far as Gilead, there was not a city too high for us. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4975BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4975BC\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God gave all into our hands.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Only to the land of the sons of Ammon you did not draw near, that is, to all the banks of the river <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4976BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4976BD\"></sup>Jabbok and the cities of the hill country, whatever the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God had forbidden us."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>“Then we turned and went up the way to Bashan. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4977A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4977A\"></sup>Og the king of Bashan came out against us, he and all his people, to battle at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4977B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4977B\"></sup>Edrei.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘Do not fear him, for I have given him and all his people and his land into your hand. And you shall do to him as you did to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4978C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4978C\"></sup>Sihon the king of the Amorites, who lived at Heshbon.’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God gave into our hand Og also, the king of Bashan, and all his people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4979D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4979D\"></sup>and we struck him down until he had no survivor left.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And we took all his cities at that time—there was not a city that we did not take from them—sixty cities, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4980E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4980E\"></sup>the whole region of Argob, the kingdom of Og in Bashan.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>All these were cities fortified with high walls, gates, and bars, besides very many unwalled villages.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4982F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4982F\"></sup>we devoted them to destruction, as we did to Sihon the king of Heshbon, devoting to destruction every <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4982G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4982G\"></sup>city, men, women, and children.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But all the livestock and the spoil of the cities we took as our plunder.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So we took the land at that time out of the hand of the two kings of the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan, from the Valley of the Arnon to Mount Hermon",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>(the Sidonians call <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4985H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4985H\"></sup>Hermon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4985I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4985I\"></sup>Sirion, while the Amorites call it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4985J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4985J\"></sup>Senir),",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>all the cities of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4986K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4986K\"></sup>tableland and all Gilead and all Bashan, as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4986L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4986L\"></sup>Salecah and Edrei, cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>(For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4987M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4987M\"></sup>only Og the king of Bashan was left of the remnant of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4987N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4987N\"></sup>the Rephaim. Behold, his bed was a bed of iron. Is it not in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4987O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4987O\"></sup>Rabbah of the Ammonites? Nine cubits was its length, and four cubits its breadth, according to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4987P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4987P\"></sup>common cubit.)",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“When we took possession of this land at that time, I gave to the Reubenites and the Gadites the territory beginning <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4988Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4988Q\"></sup>at Aroer, which is on the edge of the Valley of the Arnon, and half the hill country of Gilead with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4988R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4988R\"></sup>its cities.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4989S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4989S\"></sup>The rest of Gilead, and all Bashan, the kingdom of Og, that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4989T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4989T\"></sup>all the region of Argob, I gave to the half-tribe of Manasseh. (All that portion of Bashan is called the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4989U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4989U\"></sup>Rephaim.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4990V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4990V\"></sup>Jair the Manassite took all the region of Argob, that is, Bashan, as far as the border of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4990W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4990W\"></sup>the Geshurites and the Maacathites, and called the villages <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4990X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4990X\"></sup>after his own name, Havvoth-jair, as it is to this day.)",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>To Machir <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4991Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4991Y\"></sup>I gave Gilead,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and to the Reubenites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4992Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4992Z\"></sup>and the Gadites I gave the territory from Gilead as far as the Valley of the Arnon, with the middle of the valley as a border, as far over as the river Jabbok, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4992AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4992AA\"></sup>the border of the Ammonites;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the Arabah also, with the Jordan as the border, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4993AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4993AB\"></sup>Chinnereth as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4993AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4993AC\"></sup>the Sea of the Arabah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4993AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4993AD\"></sup>the Salt Sea, under <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4993AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4993AE\"></sup>the slopes of Pisgah on the east.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“And I commanded you at that time, saying, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given you this land to possess. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4994AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4994AF\"></sup>All your men of valor shall cross over armed before your brothers, the people of Israel.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Only your wives, your little ones, and your livestock <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4995AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4995AG\"></sup>(I know that you have much livestock) shall remain in the cities that I have given you,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4996AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4996AH\"></sup>until the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives rest to your brothers, as to you, and they also occupy the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives them beyond the Jordan. Then each of you may return to his possession which I have given you.’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And I commanded <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4997AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4997AI\"></sup>Joshua at that time, ‘Your eyes have seen all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has done to these two kings. So will the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> do to all the kingdoms into which you are crossing.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>You shall not fear them, for it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-4998AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-4998AJ\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God who fights for you.’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“And I pleaded with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at that time, saying,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>‘O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, you have only begun to show your servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5000AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5000AK\"></sup>your greatness and your mighty hand. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5000AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5000AL\"></sup>what god is there in heaven or on earth who can do such works and mighty acts as yours?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Please let me go over and see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5001AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5001AM\"></sup>the good land beyond the Jordan, that good hill country and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5001AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5001AN\"></sup>Lebanon.’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5002AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5002AO\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was angry with me because of you and would not listen to me. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5002AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5002AP\"></sup>‘Enough from you; do not speak to me of this matter again.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5003AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5003AQ\"></sup>Go up to the top of Pisgah and lift up your eyes westward and northward and southward and eastward, and look at it with your eyes, for you shall not go over this Jordan.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5004AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5004AR\"></sup>charge Joshua, and encourage and strengthen him, for he shall go over at the head of this people, and he shall put them in possession of the land that you shall see.’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So we remained in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5005AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5005AS\"></sup>the valley opposite Beth-peor."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>“And now, O Israel, listen to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5006A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5006A\"></sup>the statutes and the rules that I am teaching you, and do them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5006B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5006B\"></sup>that you may live, and go in and take possession of the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, is giving you.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5007C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5007C\"></sup>You shall not add to the word that I command you, nor take from it, that you may keep the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God that I command you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Your eyes have seen what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5008D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5008D\"></sup>at Baal-peor, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God destroyed from among you all the men who followed the Baal of Peor.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But you who held fast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God are all alive today.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>See, I have taught you statutes and rules, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God commanded me, that you should do them in the land that you are entering to take possession of it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5011E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5011E\"></sup>Keep them and do them, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5011F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5011F\"></sup>that will be your wisdom and your understanding in the sight of the peoples, who, when they hear all these statutes, will say, ‘Surely this great nation is a wise and understanding people.’",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5012G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5012G\"></sup>what great nation is there that has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5012H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5012H\"></sup>a god so near to it as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God is to us, whenever we call upon him?",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And what great nation is there, that has statutes and rules so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5013I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5013I\"></sup>righteous as all this law that I set before you today?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5014J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5014J\"></sup>“Only take care, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5014K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5014K\"></sup>keep your soul diligently, lest you forget the things that your eyes have seen, and lest they depart from your heart all the days of your life. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5014L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5014L\"></sup>Make them known to your children and your children's children—",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>how on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5015M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5015M\"></sup>the day that you stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God at Horeb, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5015N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5015N\"></sup>‘Gather the people to me, that I may let them hear my words, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5015O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5015O\"></sup>so that they may learn to fear <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5015P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5015P\"></sup>me all the days that they live on the earth, and that they may teach their children so.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5016Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5016Q\"></sup>you came near and stood at the foot of the mountain, while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5016R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5016R\"></sup>the mountain burned with fire to the heart of heaven, wrapped in darkness, cloud, and gloom.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5017S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5017S\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to you out of the midst of the fire. You heard the sound of words, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5017T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5017T\"></sup>but saw no form; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5017U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5017U\"></sup>there was only a voice.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5018V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5018V\"></sup>And he declared to you his covenant, which he commanded you to perform, that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5018W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5018W\"></sup>the Ten Commandments, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5018X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5018X\"></sup>and he wrote them on two tablets of stone.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5019Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5019Y\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded me at that time to teach you statutes and rules, that you might do them in the land that you are going over to possess.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5020Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5020Z\"></sup>“Therefore watch yourselves very carefully. Since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5020AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5020AA\"></sup>you saw no form on the day that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to you at Horeb out of the midst of the fire,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>beware <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5021AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5021AB\"></sup>lest you act corruptly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5021AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5021AC\"></sup>by making a carved image for yourselves, in the form of any figure, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5021AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5021AD\"></sup>the likeness of male or female,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the likeness of any animal that is on the earth, the likeness of any winged bird that flies in the air,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the likeness of anything that creeps on the ground, the likeness of any fish that is in the water under the earth.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And beware lest you raise your eyes to heaven, and when you see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5024AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5024AE\"></sup>the sun and the moon and the stars, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5024AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5024AF\"></sup>all the host of heaven, you be drawn away and bow down to them and serve them, things that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has allotted to all the peoples under the whole heaven.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has taken you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5025AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5025AG\"></sup>brought you out of the iron furnace, out of Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5025AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5025AH\"></sup>to be a people of his own inheritance, as you are this day.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Furthermore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5026AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5026AI\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was angry with me because of you, and he swore that I should not cross the Jordan, and that I should not enter the good land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you for an inheritance.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For I must die in this land; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5027AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5027AJ\"></sup>I must not go over the Jordan. But you shall go over and take possession of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5027AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5027AK\"></sup>that good land.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5028AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5028AL\"></sup>Take care, lest you forget the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, which he made with you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5028AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5028AM\"></sup>make a carved image, the form of anything that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has forbidden you.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5029AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5029AN\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is a consuming fire, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5029AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5029AO\"></sup>a jealous God.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“When you father children and children's children, and have grown old in the land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5030AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5030AP\"></sup>if you act corruptly by making a carved image in the form of anything, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5030AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5030AQ\"></sup>by doing what is evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, so as to provoke him to anger,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5031AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5031AR\"></sup>call heaven and earth to witness against you today, that you will soon utterly perish from the land that you are going over the Jordan to possess. You will not live long in it, but will be utterly destroyed.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5032AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5032AS\"></sup>will scatter you among the peoples, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5032AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5032AT\"></sup>and you will be left few in number among the nations where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will drive you.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5033AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5033AU\"></sup>there you will serve gods of wood and stone, the work of human hands, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5033AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5033AV\"></sup>that neither see, nor hear, nor eat, nor smell.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5034AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5034AW\"></sup>But from there you will seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and you will find him, if you search after him with all your heart and with all your soul.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When you are in tribulation, and all these things come upon you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5035AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5035AX\"></sup>in the latter days, you will return to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and obey his voice.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5036AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5036AY\"></sup>a merciful God. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5036AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5036AZ\"></sup>He will not leave you or destroy you or forget the covenant with your fathers that he swore to them.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5037BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5037BA\"></sup>ask now of the days that are past, which were before you, since the day that God created man on the earth, and ask from one end of heaven to the other, whether such a great thing as this has ever happened or was ever heard of.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5038BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5038BB\"></sup>Did any people ever hear the voice of a god speaking out of the midst of the fire, as you have heard, and still live?",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Or has any god ever attempted to go and take a nation for himself from the midst of another nation, by trials, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5039BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5039BC\"></sup>by signs, by wonders, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5039BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5039BD\"></sup>by war, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5039BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5039BE\"></sup>by a mighty hand and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5039BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5039BF\"></sup>an outstretched arm, and by great deeds of terror, all of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God did for you in Egypt before your eyes?",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>To you it was shown, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5040BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5040BG\"></sup>that you might know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is God; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5040BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5040BH\"></sup>there is no other besides him.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5041BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5041BI\"></sup>Out of heaven he let you hear his voice, that he might discipline you. And on earth he let you see his great fire, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5041BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5041BJ\"></sup>you heard his words out of the midst of the fire.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5042BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5042BK\"></sup>he loved your fathers and chose their offspring after them and brought you out of Egypt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5042BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5042BL\"></sup>with his own presence, by his great power,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5043BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5043BM\"></sup>driving out before you nations greater and mightier than you, to bring you in, to give you their land for an inheritance, as it is this day,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>know therefore today, and lay it to your heart, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5044BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5044BN\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is God in heaven above and on the earth beneath; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5044BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5044BO\"></sup>there is no other.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5045BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5045BP\"></sup>Therefore you shall keep his statutes and his commandments, which I command you today, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5045BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5045BQ\"></sup>that it may go well with you and with your children after you, and that you may prolong your days in the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you for all time.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Then Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5046BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5046BR\"></sup>set apart three cities in the east beyond the Jordan,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5047BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5047BS\"></sup>the manslayer might flee there, anyone who kills his neighbor unintentionally, without being at enmity with him in time past; he may flee to one of these cities and save his life:",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5048BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5048BT\"></sup>Bezer in the wilderness on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5048BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5048BU\"></sup>tableland for the Reubenites, Ramoth in Gilead for the Gadites, and Golan in Bashan for the Manassites.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>This is the law that Moses set before the people of Israel.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>These are the testimonies, the statutes, and the rules, which Moses spoke to the people of Israel when they came out of Egypt,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>beyond the Jordan <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5051BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5051BV\"></sup>in the valley opposite Beth-peor, in the land of Sihon the king of the Amorites, who lived at Heshbon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5051BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5051BW\"></sup>whom Moses and the people of Israel defeated when they came out of Egypt.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>And they took possession of his land and the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5052BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5052BX\"></sup>of Og, the king of Bashan, the two kings of the Amorites, who lived to the east beyond the Jordan;",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5053BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5053BY\"></sup>from Aroer, which is on the edge of the Valley of the Arnon, as far as Mount <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5053BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5053BZ\"></sup>Sirion (that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5053CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5053CA\"></sup>Hermon),",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>together with all the Arabah on the east side of the Jordan as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5054CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5054CB\"></sup>the Sea of the Arabah, under the slopes of Pisgah."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>And Moses summoned all Israel and said to them, “Hear, O Israel, the statutes and the rules that I speak in your hearing today, and you shall learn them and be careful to do them.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5056A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5056A\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God made a covenant with us in Horeb.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5057B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5057B\"></sup>Not with our fathers did the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> make this covenant, but with us, who are all of us here alive today.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke with you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5058C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5058C\"></sup>face to face at the mountain, out of the midst of the fire,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5059D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5059D\"></sup>while I stood between the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and you at that time, to declare to you the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5059E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5059E\"></sup>you were afraid because of the fire, and you did not go up into the mountain. He said:",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5060F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5060F\"></sup>“‘I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“‘You shall have no other gods before me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“‘You shall not make for yourself a carved image, or any likeness of anything that is in heaven above, or that is on the earth beneath, or that is in the water under the earth.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You shall not bow down to them or serve them; for I the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God am a jealous God, visiting the iniquity of the fathers on the children to the third and fourth generation of those who hate me,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>but showing steadfast love to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5064G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5064G\"></sup>thousands of those who love me and keep my commandments.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“‘You shall not take the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in vain, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will not hold him guiltless who takes his name in vain.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“‘Observe the Sabbath day, to keep it holy, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God commanded you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Six days you shall labor and do all your work,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5068H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5068H\"></sup>the seventh day is a Sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. On it you shall not do any work, you or your son or your daughter or your male servant or your female servant, or your ox or your donkey or any of your livestock, or the sojourner who is within your gates, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5068I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5068I\"></sup>that your male servant and your female servant may rest as well as you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5069J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5069J\"></sup>You shall remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God brought you out from there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5069K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5069K\"></sup>with a mighty hand and an outstretched arm. Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God commanded you to keep the Sabbath day.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“‘Honor your father and your mother, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God commanded you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5070L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5070L\"></sup>that your days may be long, and that it may go well with you in the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5071M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5071M\"></sup>“‘You shall not murder.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5072N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5072N\"></sup>“‘And you shall not commit adultery.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“‘And you shall not steal.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“‘And you shall not bear false witness against your neighbor.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“‘And you shall not covet your neighbor's wife. And you shall not desire your neighbor's house, his field, or his male servant, or his female servant, his ox, or his donkey, or anything that is your neighbor's.’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“These words the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to all your assembly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5076O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5076O\"></sup>at the mountain out of the midst of the fire, the cloud, and the thick darkness, with a loud voice; and he added no more. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5076P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5076P\"></sup>he wrote them on two tablets of stone and gave them to me.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5077Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5077Q\"></sup>as soon as you heard the voice out of the midst of the darkness, while the mountain was burning with fire, you came near to me, all the heads of your tribes, and your elders.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And you said, ‘Behold, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God has shown us his glory and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5078R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5078R\"></sup>greatness, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5078S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5078S\"></sup>we have heard his voice out of the midst of the fire. This day we have seen God speak with man, and man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5078T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5078T\"></sup>still live.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now therefore why should we die? For this great fire will consume us. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5079U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5079U\"></sup>If we hear the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God any more, we shall die.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5080V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5080V\"></sup>For who is there of all flesh, that has heard the voice of the living God speaking out of the midst of fire as we have, and has still lived?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Go near and hear all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God will say, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5081W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5081W\"></sup>speak to us all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God will speak to you, and we will hear and do it.’",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard your words, when you spoke to me. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘I have heard the words of this people, which they have spoken to you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5082X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5082X\"></sup>They are right in all that they have spoken.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5083Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5083Y\"></sup>Oh that they had such a heart as this always, to fear me and to keep all my commandments, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5083Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5083Z\"></sup>that it might go well with them and with their descendants forever!",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Go and say to them, “Return to your tents.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But you, stand here by me, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5085AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5085AA\"></sup>I will tell you the whole commandment and the statutes and the rules that you shall teach them, that they may do them in the land that I am giving them to possess.’",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>You shall be careful therefore to do as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has commanded you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5086AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5086AB\"></sup>You shall not turn aside to the right hand or to the left.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5087AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5087AC\"></sup>You shall walk in all the way that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has commanded you, that you may live, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5087AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5087AD\"></sup>that it may go well with you, and that you may live long in the land that you shall possess."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>“Now this is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5088A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5088A\"></sup>the commandment—the statutes and the rules—that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God commanded me to teach you, that you may do them in the land to which you are going over, to possess it,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5089B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5089B\"></sup>you may fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, you and your son and your son's son, by keeping all his statutes and his commandments, which I command you, all the days of your life, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5089C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5089C\"></sup>that your days may be long.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Hear therefore, O Israel, and be careful to do them, that it may go well with you, and that you may multiply greatly, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5090D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5090D\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, has promised you, in a land flowing with milk and honey.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Hear, O Israel: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5091E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5091E\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is one.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5092F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5092F\"></sup>shall love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with all your heart and with all your soul and with all your might.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5093G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5093G\"></sup>these words that I command you today shall be on your heart.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5094H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5094H\"></sup>You shall teach them diligently to your children, and shall talk of them when you sit in your house, and when you walk by the way, and when you lie down, and when you rise.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5095I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5095I\"></sup>You shall bind them as a sign on your hand, and they shall be as frontlets between your eyes.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5096J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5096J\"></sup>You shall write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“And when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God brings you into the land that he swore to your fathers, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, to give you—with great and good cities <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5097K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5097K\"></sup>that you did not build,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and houses full of all good things that you did not fill, and cisterns that you did not dig, and vineyards and olive trees that you did not plant—and when you eat and are full,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5099L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5099L\"></sup>then take care lest you forget the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>It is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5100M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5100M\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God you shall fear. Him you shall serve and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5100N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5100N\"></sup>by his name you shall swear.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You shall not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5101O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5101O\"></sup>go after other gods, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5101P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5101P\"></sup>the gods of the peoples who are around you—",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5102Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5102Q\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in your midst <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5102R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5102R\"></sup>is a jealous God—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5102S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5102S\"></sup>lest the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God be kindled against you, and he destroy you from off the face of the earth.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5103T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5103T\"></sup>“You shall not put the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God to the test, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5103U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5103U\"></sup>as you tested him at Massah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5104V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5104V\"></sup>diligently keep the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and his testimonies and his statutes, which he has commanded you.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5105W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5105W\"></sup>And you shall do what is right and good in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that it may go well with you, and that you may go in and take possession of the good land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to give to your fathers",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5106X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5106X\"></sup>by thrusting out all your enemies from before you, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has promised.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5107Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5107Y\"></sup>“When your son asks you in time to come, ‘What is the meaning of the testimonies and the statutes and the rules that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God has commanded you?’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>then you shall say to your son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5108Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5108Z\"></sup>‘We were Pharaoh's slaves in Egypt. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought us out of Egypt with a mighty hand.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5109AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5109AA\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> showed signs and wonders, great and grievous, against Egypt and against Pharaoh and all his household, before our eyes.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And he brought us out from there, that he might bring us in and give us the land that he swore to give to our fathers.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded us to do all these statutes, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5111AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5111AB\"></sup>to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5111AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5111AC\"></sup>for our good always, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5111AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5111AD\"></sup>he might preserve us alive, as we are this day.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5112AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5112AE\"></sup>it will be righteousness for us, if we are careful to do all this commandment before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, as he has commanded us.’"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>“When the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5113A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5113A\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God brings you into the land that you are entering to take possession of it, and clears away many nations before you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5113B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5113B\"></sup>the Hittites, the Girgashites, the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites, seven nations <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5113C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5113C\"></sup>more numerous and mightier than you,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5114D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5114D\"></sup>and when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives them over to you, and you defeat them, then you must <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5114E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5114E\"></sup>devote them to complete destruction. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5114F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5114F\"></sup>You shall make no covenant with them and show no mercy to them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5115G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5115G\"></sup>You shall not intermarry with them, giving your daughters to their sons or taking their daughters for your sons,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>for they would turn away your sons from following me, to serve other gods. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5116H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5116H\"></sup>Then the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> would be kindled against you, and he would destroy you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5116I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5116I\"></sup>quickly.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But thus shall you deal with them: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5117J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5117J\"></sup>you shall break down their altars and dash in pieces their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5117K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5117K\"></sup>pillars and chop down their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5117L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5117L\"></sup>Asherim and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5117M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5117M\"></sup>burn their carved images with fire.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5118N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5118N\"></sup>you are a people holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has chosen you to be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5118O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5118O\"></sup>a people for his treasured possession, out of all the peoples who are on the face of the earth.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>It was not because you were more in number than any other people that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> set his love on you and chose you, for you were the fewest of all peoples,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5120P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5120P\"></sup>it is because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loves you and is keeping <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5120Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5120Q\"></sup>the oath that he swore to your fathers, that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has brought you out with a mighty hand and redeemed you from the house of slavery, from the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Know therefore that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5121R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5121R\"></sup>the faithful God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5121S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5121S\"></sup>who keeps covenant and steadfast love with those who love him and keep his commandments, to a thousand generations,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5122T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5122T\"></sup>repays to their face those who hate him, by destroying them. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5122U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5122U\"></sup>He will not be slack with one who hates him. He will repay him to his face.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5123V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5123V\"></sup>You shall therefore be careful to do the commandment and the statutes and the rules that I command you today.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5124W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5124W\"></sup>“And because you listen to these rules and keep and do them, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will keep with you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5124X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5124X\"></sup>the covenant and the steadfast love that he swore to your fathers.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5125Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5125Y\"></sup>love you, bless you, and multiply you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5125Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5125Z\"></sup>He will also bless the fruit of your womb and the fruit of your ground, your grain and your wine and your oil, the increase of your herds and the young of your flock, in the land that he swore to your fathers to give you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You shall be blessed above all peoples. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5126AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5126AA\"></sup>There shall not be male or female barren among you or among your livestock.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will take away from you all sickness, and none of the evil <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5127AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5127AB\"></sup>diseases of Egypt, which you knew, will he inflict on you, but he will lay them on all who hate you.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5128AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5128AC\"></sup>you shall consume all the peoples that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will give over to you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5128AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5128AD\"></sup>Your eye shall not pity them, neither shall you serve their gods, for that would be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5128AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5128AE\"></sup>a snare to you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“If you say in your heart, ‘These nations are greater than I. How can I dispossess them?’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5130AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5130AF\"></sup>you shall not be afraid of them but you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5130AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5130AG\"></sup>remember what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God did to Pharaoh and to all Egypt,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>the great trials that your eyes saw, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5131AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5131AH\"></sup>the signs, the wonders, the mighty hand, and the outstretched arm, by which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God brought you out. So will the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God do to all the peoples of whom you are afraid.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5132AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5132AI\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will send hornets among them, until those who are left and hide themselves from you are destroyed.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>You shall not be in dread of them, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5133AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5133AJ\"></sup>in your midst, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5133AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5133AK\"></sup>a great and awesome God.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5134AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5134AL\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will clear away these nations before you little by little. You may not make an end of them at once, lest the wild beasts grow too numerous for you.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5135AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5135AM\"></sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will give them over to you and throw them into great confusion, until they are destroyed.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5136AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5136AN\"></sup>he will give their kings into your hand, and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5136AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5136AO\"></sup>make their name perish from under heaven. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5136AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5136AP\"></sup>No one shall be able to stand against you until you have destroyed them.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The carved images of their gods <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5137AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5137AQ\"></sup>you shall burn with fire. You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5137AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5137AR\"></sup>shall not covet the silver or the gold that is on them or take it for yourselves, lest you be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5137AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5137AS\"></sup>ensnared by it, for it is an abomination to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And you shall not bring an abominable thing into your house and become devoted to destruction like it. You shall utterly detest and abhor it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5138AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5138AT\"></sup>for it is devoted to destruction."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>“The whole commandment that I command you today <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5139A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5139A\"></sup>you shall be careful to do, that you may live and multiply, and go in and possess the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to give to your fathers.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And you shall remember the whole way that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has led you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5140B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5140B\"></sup>these forty years in the wilderness, that he might humble you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5140C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5140C\"></sup>testing you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5140D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5140D\"></sup>to know what was in your heart, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5140E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5140E\"></sup>whether you would keep his commandments or not.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he humbled you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5141F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5141F\"></sup>let you hunger and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5141G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5141G\"></sup>fed you with manna, which you did not know, nor did your fathers know, that he might make you know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5141H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5141H\"></sup>man does not live by bread alone, but man lives by every word that comes from the mouth of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5142I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5142I\"></sup>Your clothing did not wear out on you and your foot did not swell these forty years.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Know then in your heart that, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5143J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5143J\"></sup>as a man disciplines his son, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God disciplines you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So you shall keep the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God by walking in his ways and by fearing him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is bringing you into a good land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5145K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5145K\"></sup>a land of brooks of water, of fountains and springs, flowing out in the valleys and hills,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>a land of wheat and barley, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5146L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5146L\"></sup>of vines and fig trees and pomegranates, a land of olive trees and honey,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>a land in which you will eat bread without scarcity, in which you will lack nothing, a land whose stones are iron, and out of whose hills you can dig copper.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And you shall eat and be full, and you shall bless the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God for the good land he has given you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Take care lest you forget the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God by not keeping his commandments and his rules and his statutes, which I command you today,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5150M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5150M\"></sup>lest, when you have eaten and are full and have built good houses and live in them,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and when your herds and flocks multiply and your silver and gold is multiplied and all that you have is multiplied,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5152N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5152N\"></sup>then your heart be lifted up, and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5152O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5152O\"></sup>forget the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5153P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5153P\"></sup>led you through the great and terrifying wilderness, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5153Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5153Q\"></sup>with its fiery serpents and scorpions <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5153R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5153R\"></sup>and thirsty ground where there was no water, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5153S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5153S\"></sup>who brought you water out of the flinty rock,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>who fed you in the wilderness with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5154T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5154T\"></sup>manna that your fathers did not know, that he might humble you and test you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5154U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5154U\"></sup>to do you good in the end.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Beware <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5155V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5155V\"></sup>lest you say in your heart, ‘My power and the might of my hand have gotten me this wealth.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You shall remember the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5156W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5156W\"></sup>it is he who gives you power to get wealth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5156X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5156X\"></sup>that he may confirm his covenant that he swore to your fathers, as it is this day.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And if you forget the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and go after other gods and serve them and worship them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5157Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5157Y\"></sup>I solemnly warn you today that you shall surely perish.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Like the nations that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> makes to perish before you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5158Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5158Z\"></sup>so shall you perish, because you would not obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>“Hear, O Israel: you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5159A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5159A\"></sup>to cross over the Jordan today, to go in to dispossess nations <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5159B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5159B\"></sup>greater and mightier than you, cities great and fortified up to heaven,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>a people great and tall, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5160C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5160C\"></sup>the sons of the Anakim, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5160D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5160D\"></sup>whom you know, and of whom you have heard it said, ‘Who can stand before the sons of Anak?’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Know therefore today that he who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5161E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5161E\"></sup>goes over before you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5161F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5161F\"></sup>as a consuming fire is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. He will destroy them and subdue them before you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5161G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5161G\"></sup>So you shall drive them out and make them perish quickly, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has promised you.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5162H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5162H\"></sup>“Do not say in your heart, after the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has thrust them out before you, ‘It is because of my righteousness that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has brought me in to possess this land,’ whereas it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5162I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5162I\"></sup>because of the wickedness of these nations that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is driving them out before you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5163J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5163J\"></sup>Not because of your righteousness or the uprightness of your heart are you going in to possess their land, but because of the wickedness of these nations the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is driving them out from before you, and that he may confirm <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5163K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5163K\"></sup>the word that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to your fathers, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Know, therefore, that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is not giving you this good land to possess because of your righteousness, for you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5164L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5164L\"></sup>a stubborn people.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Remember and do not forget how you provoked the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God to wrath in the wilderness. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5165M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5165M\"></sup>From the day you came out of the land of Egypt until you came to this place, you have been rebellious against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5166N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5166N\"></sup>at Horeb you provoked the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to wrath, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was so angry with you that he was ready to destroy you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5167O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5167O\"></sup>When I went up the mountain to receive the tablets of stone, the tablets of the covenant that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made with you, I remained on the mountain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5167P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5167P\"></sup>forty days and forty nights. I neither ate bread nor drank water.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5168Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5168Q\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave me the two tablets of stone written with the finger of God, and on them were all the words that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken with you on the mountain out of the midst of the fire <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5168R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5168R\"></sup>on the day of the assembly.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And at the end of forty days and forty nights the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave me the two tablets of stone, the tablets of the covenant.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5170S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5170S\"></sup>‘Arise, go down quickly from here, for your people whom you have brought from Egypt have acted corruptly. They have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5170T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5170T\"></sup>turned aside quickly out of the way that I commanded them; they have made themselves a metal image.’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5171U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5171U\"></sup>“Furthermore, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘I have seen this people, and behold, it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5171V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5171V\"></sup>a stubborn people.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5172W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5172W\"></sup>Let me alone, that I may destroy them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5172X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5172X\"></sup>blot out their name from under heaven. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5172Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5172Y\"></sup>I will make of you a nation mightier and greater than they.’",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5173Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5173Z\"></sup>So I turned and came down from the mountain, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5173AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5173AA\"></sup>the mountain was burning with fire. And the two tablets of the covenant were in my two hands.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5174AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5174AB\"></sup>I looked, and behold, you had sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. You had made yourselves a golden calf. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5174AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5174AC\"></sup>You had turned aside quickly from the way that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So I took hold of the two tablets and threw them out of my two hands and broke them before your eyes.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5176AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5176AD\"></sup>lay prostrate before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5176AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5176AE\"></sup>as before, forty days and forty nights. I neither ate bread nor drank water, because of all the sin that you had committed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5176AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5176AF\"></sup>in doing what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to provoke him to anger.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>For I was afraid of the anger and hot displeasure that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> bore against you, so that he was ready to destroy you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5177AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5177AG\"></sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> listened to me that time also.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was so angry with Aaron that he was ready to destroy him. And I prayed for Aaron also at the same time.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5179AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5179AH\"></sup>I took the sinful thing, the calf that you had made, and burned it with fire and crushed it, grinding it very small, until it was as fine as dust. And I threw the dust of it into the brook that ran down from the mountain.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“At <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5180AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5180AI\"></sup>Taberah also, and at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5180AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5180AJ\"></sup>Massah and at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5180AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5180AK\"></sup>Kibroth-hattaavah you provoked the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to wrath.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5181AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5181AL\"></sup>when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent you from Kadesh-barnea, saying, ‘Go up and take possession of the land that I have given you,’ then you rebelled against the commandment of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5181AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5181AM\"></sup>did not believe him or obey his voice.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5182AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5182AN\"></sup>You have been rebellious against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from the day that I knew you.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5183AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5183AO\"></sup>“So I lay prostrate before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for these forty days and forty nights, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said he would destroy you.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5184AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5184AP\"></sup>And I prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, do not destroy your people and your heritage, whom you have redeemed through your greatness, whom you have brought out of Egypt with a mighty hand.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Remember your servants, Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. Do not regard the stubbornness of this people, or their wickedness or their sin,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>lest the land from which you brought us say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5186AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5186AQ\"></sup>“Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not able to bring them into the land that he promised them, and because he hated them, he has brought them out to put them to death in the wilderness.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5187AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5187AR\"></sup>For they are your people and your heritage, whom you brought out by your great power and by your outstretched arm.’"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>“At that time the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5188A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5188A\"></sup>‘Cut for yourself two tablets of stone like the first, and come up to me on the mountain and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5188B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5188B\"></sup>make an ark of wood.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And I will write on the tablets the words that were on the first tablets that you broke, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5189C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5189C\"></sup>you shall put them in the ark.’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So I made an ark <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5190D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5190D\"></sup>of acacia wood, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5190E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5190E\"></sup>cut two tablets of stone like the first, and went up the mountain with the two tablets in my hand.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5191F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5191F\"></sup>he wrote on the tablets, in the same writing as before, the Ten Commandments <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5191G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5191G\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken to you on the mountain out of the midst of the fire <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5191H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5191H\"></sup>on the day of the assembly. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them to me.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then I turned and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5192I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5192I\"></sup>came down from the mountain and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5192J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5192J\"></sup>put the tablets in the ark that I had made. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5192K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5192K\"></sup>And there they are, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded me.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>(The people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5193L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5193L\"></sup>journeyed from Beeroth Bene-jaakan to Moserah. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5193M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5193M\"></sup>There Aaron died, and there he was buried. And his son Eleazar ministered as priest in his place.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5194N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5194N\"></sup>From there they journeyed to Gudgodah, and from Gudgodah to Jotbathah, a land with brooks of water.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>At that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5195O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5195O\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> set apart the tribe of Levi <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5195P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5195P\"></sup>to carry the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5195Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5195Q\"></sup>to stand before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to minister to him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5195R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5195R\"></sup>to bless in his name, to this day.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5196S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5196S\"></sup>Therefore Levi has no portion or inheritance with his brothers. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is his inheritance, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God said to him.)",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5197T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5197T\"></sup>“I myself stayed on the mountain, as at the first time, forty days and forty nights, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5197U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5197U\"></sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> listened to me that time also. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was unwilling to destroy you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5198V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5198V\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, ‘Arise, go on your journey at the head of the people, so that they may go in and possess the land, which I swore to their fathers to give them.’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“And now, Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5199W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5199W\"></sup>what does the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God require of you, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5199X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5199X\"></sup>to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5199Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5199Y\"></sup>to walk in all his ways, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5199Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5199Z\"></sup>to love him, to serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with all your heart and with all your soul,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5200AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5200AA\"></sup>to keep the commandments and statutes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which I am commanding you today <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5200AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5200AB\"></sup>for your good?",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5201AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5201AC\"></sup>to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God belong heaven and the heaven of heavens, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5201AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5201AD\"></sup>the earth with all that is in it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5202AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5202AE\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> set his heart in love on your fathers and chose their offspring after them, you above all peoples, as you are this day.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Circumcise therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5203AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5203AF\"></sup>the foreskin of your heart, and be no longer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5203AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5203AG\"></sup>stubborn.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5204AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5204AH\"></sup>God of gods and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5204AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5204AI\"></sup>Lord of lords, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5204AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5204AJ\"></sup>the great, the mighty, and the awesome God, who is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5204AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5204AK\"></sup>not partial and takes no bribe.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5205AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5205AL\"></sup>He executes justice for the fatherless and the widow, and loves the sojourner, giving him food and clothing.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5206AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5206AM\"></sup>Love the sojourner, therefore, for you were sojourners in the land of Egypt.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5207AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5207AN\"></sup>You shall fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. You shall serve him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5207AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5207AO\"></sup>hold fast to him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5207AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5207AP\"></sup>by his name you shall swear.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5208AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5208AQ\"></sup>He is your praise. He is your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5208AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5208AR\"></sup>who has done for you these great and terrifying things that your eyes have seen.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Your fathers went down to Egypt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5209AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5209AS\"></sup>seventy persons, and now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has made you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5209AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5209AT\"></sup>as numerous as the stars of heaven."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5210A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5210A\"></sup>“You shall therefore love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5210B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5210B\"></sup>keep his charge, his statutes, his rules, and his commandments always.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And consider today (since I am not speaking to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5211C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5211C\"></sup>your children who have not known or seen it), consider the discipline of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5211D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5211D\"></sup>his greatness, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5211E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5211E\"></sup>his mighty hand and his outstretched arm,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5212F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5212F\"></sup>his signs and his deeds that he did in Egypt to Pharaoh the king of Egypt and to all his land,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and what he did to the army of Egypt, to their horses and to their chariots, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5213G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5213G\"></sup>how he made the water of the Red Sea flow over them as they pursued after you, and how the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has destroyed them to this day,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5214H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5214H\"></sup>what he did to you in the wilderness, until you came to this place,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5215I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5215I\"></sup>what he did to Dathan and Abiram the sons of Eliab, son of Reuben, how the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them up, with their households, their tents, and every living thing that followed them, in the midst of all Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For your eyes have seen <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5216J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5216J\"></sup>all the great work of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he did.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“You shall therefore keep the whole commandment that I command you today, that you may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5217K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5217K\"></sup>be strong, and go in and take possession of the land that you are going over to possess,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5218L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5218L\"></sup>that you may live long in the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5218M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5218M\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to your fathers to give to them and to their offspring, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5218N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5218N\"></sup>a land flowing with milk and honey.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For the land that you are entering to take possession of it is not like the land of Egypt, from which you have come, where you sowed your seed and irrigated it, like a garden of vegetables.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5220O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5220O\"></sup>But the land that you are going over to possess is a land of hills and valleys, which drinks water by the rain from heaven,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>a land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God cares for. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5221P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5221P\"></sup>The eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God are always upon it, from the beginning of the year to the end of the year.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“And if you will indeed obey my commandments that I command you today, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5222Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5222Q\"></sup>to love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and to serve him with all your heart and with all your soul,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5223R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5223R\"></sup>he will give the rain for your land in its season, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5223S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5223S\"></sup>the early rain and the later rain, that you may gather in your grain and your wine and your oil.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5224T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5224T\"></sup>And he will give grass in your fields for your livestock, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5224U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5224U\"></sup>you shall eat and be full.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Take care <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5225V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5225V\"></sup>lest your heart be deceived, and you turn aside and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5225W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5225W\"></sup>serve other gods and worship them;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5226X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5226X\"></sup>the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be kindled against you, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5226Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5226Y\"></sup>will shut up the heavens, so that there will be no rain, and the land will yield no fruit, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5226Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5226Z\"></sup>you will perish quickly off the good land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is giving you.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5227AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5227AA\"></sup>“You shall therefore lay up these words of mine in your heart and in your soul, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5227AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5227AB\"></sup>you shall bind them as a sign on your hand, and they shall be as frontlets between your eyes.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>You shall teach them to your children, talking of them when you are sitting in your house, and when you are walking by the way, and when you lie down, and when you rise.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5229AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5229AC\"></sup>You shall write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5230AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5230AD\"></sup>that your days and the days of your children may be multiplied in the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to your fathers to give them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5230AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5230AE\"></sup>as long as the heavens are above the earth.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For if <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5231AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5231AF\"></sup>you will be careful to do all this commandment that I command you to do, loving the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, walking in all his ways, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5231AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5231AG\"></sup>holding fast to him,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5232AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5232AH\"></sup>will drive out all these nations before you, and you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5232AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5232AI\"></sup>dispossess nations greater and mightier than you.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5233AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5233AJ\"></sup>Every place on which the sole of your foot treads shall be yours. Your territory shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5233AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5233AK\"></sup>from the wilderness to the Lebanon and from the River, the river Euphrates, to the western sea.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5234AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5234AL\"></sup>No one shall be able to stand against you. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will lay <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5234AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5234AM\"></sup>the fear of you and the dread of you on all the land that you shall tread, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5234AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5234AN\"></sup>as he promised you.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5235AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5235AO\"></sup>“See, I am setting before you today a blessing and a curse:",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5236AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5236AP\"></sup>the blessing, if you obey the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, which I command you today,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5237AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5237AQ\"></sup>the curse, if you do not obey the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, but turn aside from the way that I am commanding you today, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5237AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5237AR\"></sup>to go after other gods that you have not known.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God brings you into the land that you are entering to take possession of it, you shall set <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5238AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5238AS\"></sup>the blessing on Mount Gerizim and the curse on Mount Ebal.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Are they not beyond the Jordan, west of the road, toward the going down of the sun, in the land of the Canaanites who live in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5239AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5239AT\"></sup>Arabah, opposite Gilgal, beside <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5239AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5239AU\"></sup>the oak of Moreh?",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5240AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5240AV\"></sup>to cross over the Jordan to go in to take possession of the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you. And when you possess it and live in it,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>you shall be careful <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5241AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5241AW\"></sup>to do all the statutes and the rules that I am setting before you today."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5242A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5242A\"></sup>“These are the statutes and rules that you shall be careful to do in the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, has given you to possess, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5242B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5242B\"></sup>all the days that you live on the earth.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5243C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5243C\"></sup>You shall surely destroy all the places where the nations whom you shall dispossess served their gods, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5243D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5243D\"></sup>on the high mountains and on the hills and under every green tree.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall tear down their altars and dash in pieces <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5244E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5244E\"></sup>their pillars and burn their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5244F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5244F\"></sup>Asherim with fire. You shall chop down the carved images of their gods and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5244G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5244G\"></sup>destroy their name out of that place.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5245H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5245H\"></sup>You shall not worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in that way.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But you shall seek <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5246I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5246I\"></sup>the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will choose out of all your tribes to put his name and make his habitation there. There you shall go,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and there you shall bring your burnt offerings and your sacrifices, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5247J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5247J\"></sup>your tithes and the contribution that you present, your vow offerings, your freewill offerings, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5247K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5247K\"></sup>firstborn of your herd and of your flock.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5248L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5248L\"></sup>there you shall eat before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5248M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5248M\"></sup>you shall rejoice, you and your households, in all that you undertake, in which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has blessed you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“You shall not do according to all that we are doing here today, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5249N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5249N\"></sup>everyone doing whatever is right in his own eyes,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>for you have not as yet come to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5250O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5250O\"></sup>the rest and to the inheritance that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5251P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5251P\"></sup>you go over the Jordan and live in the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you to inherit, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5251Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5251Q\"></sup>and when he gives you rest from all your enemies around, so that you live in safety,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>then to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5252R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5252R\"></sup>the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will choose, to make his name dwell there, there you shall bring all that I command you: your burnt offerings and your sacrifices, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5252S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5252S\"></sup>your tithes and the contribution that you present, and all your finest vow offerings that you vow to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5253T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5253T\"></sup>you shall rejoice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, you and your sons and your daughters, your male servants and your female servants, and the Levite that is within your towns, since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5253U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5253U\"></sup>he has no portion or inheritance with you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5254V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5254V\"></sup>Take care that you do not offer your burnt offerings at any place that you see,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>but at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5255W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5255W\"></sup>the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will choose in one of your tribes, there you shall offer your burnt offerings, and there you shall do all that I am commanding you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“However, you may slaughter and eat meat within any of your towns, as much as you desire, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5256X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5256X\"></sup>according to the blessing of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God that he has given you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5256Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5256Y\"></sup>The unclean and the clean may eat of it, as of the gazelle and as of the deer.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5257Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5257Z\"></sup>Only you shall not eat the blood; you shall pour it out on the earth like water.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>You may not eat within your towns <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5258AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5258AA\"></sup>the tithe of your grain or of your wine or of your oil, or the firstborn of your herd or of your flock, or any of your vow offerings that you vow, or your freewill offerings or the contribution that you present,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5259AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5259AB\"></sup>you shall eat them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5259AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5259AC\"></sup>the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will choose, you and your son and your daughter, your male servant and your female servant, and the Levite who is within your towns. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5259AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5259AD\"></sup>you shall rejoice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in all that you undertake.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5260AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5260AE\"></sup>Take care that you do not neglect the Levite as long as you live in your land.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5261AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5261AF\"></sup>enlarges your territory, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5261AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5261AG\"></sup>as he has promised you, and you say, ‘I will eat meat,’ because you crave meat, you may eat meat whenever you desire.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>If <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5262AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5262AH\"></sup>the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will choose to put his name there is too far from you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5262AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5262AI\"></sup>then you may kill any of your herd or your flock, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given you, as I have commanded you, and you may eat within your towns whenever you desire.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Just <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5263AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5263AJ\"></sup>as the gazelle or the deer is eaten, so you may eat of it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5263AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5263AK\"></sup>The unclean and the clean alike may eat of it.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5264AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5264AL\"></sup>Only be sure that you do not eat the blood, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5264AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5264AM\"></sup>for the blood is the life, and you shall not eat the life with the flesh.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You shall not eat it; you shall pour it out on the earth like water.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You shall not eat it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5266AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5266AN\"></sup>that all may go well with you and with your children after you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5266AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5266AO\"></sup>when you do what is right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5267AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5267AP\"></sup>holy things that are due from you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5267AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5267AQ\"></sup>your vow offerings, you shall take, and you shall go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5267AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5267AR\"></sup>the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will choose,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5268AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5268AS\"></sup>offer your burnt offerings, the flesh and the blood, on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. The blood of your sacrifices shall be poured out on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, but the flesh you may eat.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Be careful to obey all these words that I command you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5269AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5269AT\"></sup>that it may go well with you and with your children after you forever, when you do what is good and right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5270AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5270AU\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God cuts off before you the nations whom you go in to dispossess, and you dispossess them and dwell in their land,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>take care <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5271AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5271AV\"></sup>that you be not ensnared to follow them, after they have been destroyed before you, and that you do not inquire about their gods, saying, ‘How did these nations serve their gods?—that I also may do the same.’",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5272AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5272AW\"></sup>You shall not worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in that way, for every <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5272AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5272AX\"></sup>abominable thing that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hates they have done for their gods, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5272AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5272AY\"></sup>they even burn their sons and their daughters in the fire to their gods.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup> “Everything that I command you, you shall be careful to do. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5273AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5273AZ\"></sup>You shall not add to it or take from it."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>“If a prophet or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5274A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5274A\"></sup>a dreamer of dreams arises among you and gives you a sign or a wonder,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5275B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5275B\"></sup>the sign or wonder that he tells you comes to pass, and if he says, ‘Let us go after other gods,’ which you have not known, ‘and let us serve them,’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>you shall not listen to the words of that prophet or that dreamer of dreams. For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5276C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5276C\"></sup>is testing you, to know whether you love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with all your heart and with all your soul.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5277D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5277D\"></sup>walk after the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and fear him and keep his commandments and obey his voice, and you shall serve him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5277E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5277E\"></sup>hold fast to him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5278F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5278F\"></sup>that prophet or that dreamer of dreams shall be put to death, because he has taught rebellion against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt and redeemed you out of the house of slavery, to make you leave the way in which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God commanded you to walk. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5278G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5278G\"></sup>So you shall purge the evil from your midst.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5279H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5279H\"></sup>“If your brother, the son of your mother, or your son or your daughter or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5279I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5279I\"></sup>the wife you embrace or your friend <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5279J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5279J\"></sup>who is as your own soul entices you secretly, saying, ‘Let us go and serve other gods,’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5279K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5279K\"></sup>which neither you nor your fathers have known,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>some <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5280L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5280L\"></sup>of the gods of the peoples who are around you, whether near you or far off from you, from the one end of the earth to the other,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5281M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5281M\"></sup>not yield to him or listen to him, nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5281N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5281N\"></sup>shall your eye pity him, nor shall you spare him, nor shall you conceal him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But you shall kill him. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5282O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5282O\"></sup>Your hand shall be first against him to put him to death, and afterward the hand of all the people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5283P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5283P\"></sup>You shall stone him to death with stones, because he sought to draw you away from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5284Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5284Q\"></sup>all Israel shall hear and fear and never again do any such wickedness as this among you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“If you hear in one of your cities, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you to dwell there,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>that certain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5286R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5286R\"></sup>worthless fellows have gone out among you and have drawn away the inhabitants of their city, saying, ‘Let us go and serve other gods,’ which you have not known,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>then you shall inquire and make search and ask <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5287S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5287S\"></sup>diligently. And behold, if it be true and certain that such an abomination has been done among you,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>you shall surely put the inhabitants of that city to the sword, devoting it to destruction, all who are in it and its cattle, with the edge of the sword.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>You shall gather all its spoil into the midst of its open square and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5289T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5289T\"></sup>burn the city and all its spoil with fire, as a whole burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. It shall be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5289U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5289U\"></sup>heap forever. It shall not be built again.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5290V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5290V\"></sup>None of the devoted things shall stick to your hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5290W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5290W\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may turn from the fierceness of his anger and show you mercy and have compassion on you and multiply you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5290X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5290X\"></sup>as he swore to your fathers,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>if you obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5291Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5291Y\"></sup>keeping all his commandments that I am commanding you today, and doing what is right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>“You are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5292A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5292A\"></sup>the sons of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5292B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5292B\"></sup>You shall not cut yourselves or make any <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5292C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5292C\"></sup>baldness on your foreheads for the dead.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5293D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5293D\"></sup>you are a people holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has chosen you to be a people for his treasured possession, out of all the peoples who are on the face of the earth.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5294E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5294E\"></sup>“You shall not eat any abomination.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5295F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5295F\"></sup>These are the animals you may eat: the ox, the sheep, the goat,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>the deer, the gazelle, the roebuck, the wild goat, the ibex, the antelope, and the mountain sheep.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Every animal that parts the hoof and has the hoof cloven in two and chews the cud, among the animals, you may eat.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Yet of those that chew the cud or have the hoof cloven you shall not eat these: the camel, the hare, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5298G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5298G\"></sup>rock badger, because they chew the cud but do not part the hoof, are unclean for you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the pig, because it parts the hoof but does not chew the cud, is unclean for you. Their flesh you shall not eat, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5299H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5299H\"></sup>their carcasses you shall not touch.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Of all that are in the waters you may eat these: whatever has fins and scales you may eat.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And whatever does not have fins and scales you shall not eat; it is unclean for you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“You may eat all clean birds.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But these are the ones that you shall not eat: the eagle, the bearded vulture, the black vulture,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>the kite, the falcon of any kind;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>every raven of any kind;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the ostrich, the nighthawk, the sea gull, the hawk of any kind;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the little owl and the short-eared owl, the barn owl",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and the tawny owl, the carrion vulture and the cormorant,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the stork, the heron of any kind; the hoopoe and the bat.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And all winged insects are unclean for you; they shall not be eaten.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>All clean winged things you may eat.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5312I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5312I\"></sup>“You shall not eat anything that has died naturally. You may give it to the sojourner who is within your towns, that he may eat it, or you may sell it to a foreigner. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5312J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5312J\"></sup>you are a people holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5312K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5312K\"></sup>“You shall not boil a young goat in its mother's milk.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5313L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5313L\"></sup>“You shall tithe all the yield of your seed that comes from the field year by year.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, in the place that he will choose, to make his name dwell there, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5314M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5314M\"></sup>you shall eat the tithe of your grain, of your wine, and of your oil, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5314N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5314N\"></sup>and the firstborn of your herd and flock, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5314O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5314O\"></sup>that you may learn to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God always.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And if the way is too long for you, so that you are not able to carry the tithe, when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God blesses you, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5315P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5315P\"></sup>the place is too far from you, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God chooses, to set his name there,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>then you shall turn it into money and bind up the money in your hand and go to the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God chooses",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and spend the money for whatever you desire—oxen or sheep or wine or strong drink, whatever your appetite craves. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5317Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5317Q\"></sup>you shall eat there before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and rejoice, you and your household.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And you shall not neglect <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5318R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5318R\"></sup>the Levite who is within your towns, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5318S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5318S\"></sup>he has no portion or inheritance with you.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5319T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5319T\"></sup>“At the end of every three years you shall bring out all the tithe of your produce in the same year and lay it up within your towns.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And the Levite, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5320U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5320U\"></sup>he has no portion or inheritance with you, and the sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow, who are within your towns, shall come and eat and be filled, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5320V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5320V\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God may bless you in all the work of your hands that you do."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>“At the end of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5321A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5321A\"></sup>every seven years you shall grant a release.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And this is the manner of the release: every creditor shall release what he has lent to his neighbor. He shall not exact it of his neighbor, his brother, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s release has been proclaimed.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5323B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5323B\"></sup>Of a foreigner you may exact it, but whatever of yours is with your brother your hand shall release.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5324C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5324C\"></sup>But there will be no poor among you; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5324D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5324D\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will bless you in the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you for an inheritance to possess—",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5325E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5325E\"></sup>if only you will strictly obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, being careful to do all this commandment that I command you today.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will bless you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5326F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5326F\"></sup>as he promised you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5326G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5326G\"></sup>you shall lend to many nations, but you shall not borrow, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5326H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5326H\"></sup>you shall rule over many nations, but they shall not rule over you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“If among you, one of your brothers should become poor, in any of your towns within your land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5327I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5327I\"></sup>you shall not harden your heart or shut your hand against your poor brother,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5328J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5328J\"></sup>you shall open your hand to him and lend him sufficient for his need, whatever it may be.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Take care lest there be an unworthy thought in your heart and you say, ‘The seventh year, the year of release is near,’ and your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5329K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5329K\"></sup>eye look grudgingly on your poor brother, and you give him nothing, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5329L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5329L\"></sup>cry to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> against you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5329M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5329M\"></sup>you be guilty of sin.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall give to him freely, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5330N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5330N\"></sup>your heart shall not be grudging when you give to him, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5330O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5330O\"></sup>for this the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will bless you in all your work and in all that you undertake.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5331P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5331P\"></sup>there will never cease to be poor in the land. Therefore I command you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5331Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5331Q\"></sup>‘You shall open wide your hand to your brother, to the needy and to the poor, in your land.’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5332R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5332R\"></sup>“If your brother, a Hebrew man or a Hebrew woman, is sold to you, he shall serve you six years, and in the seventh year you shall let him go free from you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And when you let him go free from you, you shall not let him go empty-handed.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You shall furnish him liberally out of your flock, out of your threshing floor, and out of your winepress. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5334S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5334S\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has blessed you, you shall give to him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5335T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5335T\"></sup>You shall remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God redeemed you; therefore I command you this today.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5336U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5336U\"></sup>if he says to you, ‘I will not go out from you,’ because he loves you and your household, since he is well-off with you,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>then you shall take an awl, and put it through his ear into the door, and he shall be your slave forever. And to your female slave you shall do the same.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>It shall not seem hard to you when you let him go free from you, for at half the cost of a hired worker he has served you six years. So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will bless you in all that you do.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5339V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5339V\"></sup>“All the firstborn males that are born of your herd and flock you shall dedicate to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. You shall do no work with the firstborn of your herd, nor shear the firstborn of your flock.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5340W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5340W\"></sup>You shall eat it, you and your household, before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God year by year at the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will choose.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5341X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5341X\"></sup>But if it has any blemish, if it is lame or blind or has any serious blemish whatever, you shall not sacrifice it to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>You shall eat it within your towns. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5342Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5342Y\"></sup>The unclean and the clean alike may eat it, as though it were a gazelle or a deer.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5343Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5343Z\"></sup>Only you shall not eat its blood; you shall pour it out on the ground like water."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>“Observe the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5344A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5344A\"></sup>month of Abib and keep the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5344B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5344B\"></sup>in the month of Abib the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God brought you out of Egypt by night.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And you shall offer the Passover sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, from the flock or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5345C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5345C\"></sup>the herd, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5345D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5345D\"></sup>at the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will choose, to make his name dwell there.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall eat no leavened bread with it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5346E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5346E\"></sup>Seven days you shall eat it with unleavened bread, the bread of affliction—for you came out of the land of Egypt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5346F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5346F\"></sup>in haste—that all the days of your life you may remember the day when you came out of the land of Egypt.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5347G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5347G\"></sup>No leaven shall be seen with you in all your territory for seven days, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5347H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5347H\"></sup>nor shall any of the flesh that you sacrifice on the evening of the first day remain all night until morning.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You may not offer the Passover sacrifice within any of your towns that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>but at the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will choose, to make his name dwell in it, there you shall offer the Passover sacrifice, in the evening at sunset, at the time you came out of Egypt.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And you shall cook it and eat it at the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will choose. And in the morning you shall turn and go to your tents.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5351I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5351I\"></sup>six days you shall eat unleavened bread, and on the seventh day there shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5351J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5351J\"></sup>a solemn assembly to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. You shall do no work on it.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5352K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5352K\"></sup>“You shall count seven weeks. Begin to count the seven weeks from the time the sickle is first put to the standing grain.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then you shall keep <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5353L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5353L\"></sup>the Feast of Weeks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5353M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5353M\"></sup>the tribute of a freewill offering from your hand, which you shall give <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5353N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5353N\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God blesses you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5354O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5354O\"></sup>you shall rejoice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, you and your son and your daughter, your male servant and your female servant, the Levite who is within your towns, the sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow who are among you, at the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will choose, to make his name dwell there.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5355P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5355P\"></sup>You shall remember that you were a slave in Egypt; and you shall be careful to observe these statutes.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5356Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5356Q\"></sup>“You shall keep the Feast of Booths seven days, when you have gathered in the produce from your threshing floor and your winepress.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5357R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5357R\"></sup>You shall rejoice in your feast, you and your son and your daughter, your male servant and your female servant, the Levite, the sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow who are within your towns.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5358S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5358S\"></sup>seven days you shall keep the feast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God at the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will choose, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will bless you in all your produce and in all the work of your hands, so that you will be altogether joyful.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5359T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5359T\"></sup>“Three times a year all your males shall appear before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God at the place that he will choose: at the Feast of Unleavened Bread, at the Feast of Weeks, and at the Feast of Booths. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5359U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5359U\"></sup>They shall not appear before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> empty-handed.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Every man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5360V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5360V\"></sup>shall give as he is able, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5360W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5360W\"></sup>according to the blessing of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God that he has given you.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“You shall appoint <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5361X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5361X\"></sup>judges and officers in all your towns that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you, according to your tribes, and they shall judge the people with righteous judgment.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5362Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5362Y\"></sup>You shall not pervert justice. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5362Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5362Z\"></sup>You shall not show partiality, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5362AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5362AA\"></sup>and you shall not accept a bribe, for a bribe blinds the eyes of the wise and subverts the cause of the righteous.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Justice, and only justice, you shall follow, that you may live and inherit the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“You shall not plant any tree as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5364AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5364AB\"></sup>an Asherah beside the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God that you shall make.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And you shall not set up a pillar, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God hates."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5366A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5366A\"></sup>“You shall not sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God an ox or a sheep in which is a blemish, any defect whatever, for that is an abomination to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5367B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5367B\"></sup>“If there is found among you, within any of your towns that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you, a man or woman who does what is evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5367C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5367C\"></sup>in transgressing his covenant,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and has gone and served other gods and worshiped them, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5368D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5368D\"></sup>the sun or the moon or any of the host of heaven, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5368E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5368E\"></sup>which I have forbidden,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and it is told you and you hear of it, then you shall inquire <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5369F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5369F\"></sup>diligently, and if it is true and certain that such an abomination has been done in Israel,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>then you shall bring out to your gates that man or woman who has done this evil thing, and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5370G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5370G\"></sup>shall stone that man or woman to death with stones.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5371H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5371H\"></sup>On the evidence of two witnesses or of three witnesses the one who is to die shall be put to death; a person shall not be put to death on the evidence of one witness.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5372I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5372I\"></sup>The hand of the witnesses shall be first against him to put him to death, and afterward the hand of all the people. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5372J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5372J\"></sup>you shall purge the evil from your midst.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“If any case arises requiring decision between one kind of homicide and another, one kind of legal right and another, or one kind of assault and another, any case within your towns that is too difficult for you, then you shall arise and go up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5373K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5373K\"></sup>the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will choose.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5374L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5374L\"></sup>And you shall come to the Levitical priests and to the judge who is in office in those days, and you shall consult them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5374M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5374M\"></sup>they shall declare to you the decision.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then you shall do according to what they declare to you from that place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will choose. And you shall be careful to do according to all that they direct you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>According to the instructions that they give you, and according to the decision which they pronounce to you, you shall do. You shall not turn aside from the verdict that they declare to you, either to the right hand or to the left.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The man who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5377N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5377N\"></sup>acts presumptuously by not obeying the priest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5377O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5377O\"></sup>who stands to minister there before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, or the judge, that man shall die. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5377P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5377P\"></sup>you shall purge the evil from Israel.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And all the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5378Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5378Q\"></sup>shall hear and fear and not act presumptuously again.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“When you come to the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you, and you possess it and dwell in it and then say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5379R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5379R\"></sup>‘I will set a king over me, like all the nations that are around me,’",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>you may indeed set a king over you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5380S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5380S\"></sup>whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will choose. One <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5380T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5380T\"></sup>from among your brothers you shall set as king over you. You may not put a foreigner over you, who is not your brother.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Only he must not acquire many <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5381U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5381U\"></sup>horses for himself or cause the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5381V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5381V\"></sup>to return to Egypt in order to acquire many horses, since the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has said to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5381W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5381W\"></sup>‘You shall never return that way again.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5382X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5382X\"></sup>shall not acquire many wives for himself, lest his heart turn away, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5382Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5382Y\"></sup>nor shall he acquire for himself excessive silver and gold.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“And when he sits on the throne of his kingdom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5383Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5383Z\"></sup>he shall write for himself in a book a copy of this law, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5383AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5383AA\"></sup>approved by the Levitical priests.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5384AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5384AB\"></sup>it shall be with him, and he shall read in it all the days of his life, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5384AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5384AC\"></sup>that he may learn to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God by keeping all the words of this law and these statutes, and doing them,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>that his heart may not be lifted up above his brothers, and that he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5385AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5385AD\"></sup>may not turn aside from the commandment, either to the right hand or to the left, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5385AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5385AE\"></sup>so that he may continue long in his kingdom, he and his children, in Israel."
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>“The Levitical priests, all the tribe of Levi, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5386A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5386A\"></sup>shall have no portion or inheritance with Israel. They <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5386B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5386B\"></sup>shall eat the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s food offerings as their inheritance.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>They shall have no inheritance among their brothers; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is their inheritance, as he promised them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And this shall be the priests' due from the people, from those offering a sacrifice, whether an ox or a sheep: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5388C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5388C\"></sup>they shall give to the priest the shoulder and the two cheeks and the stomach.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5389D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5389D\"></sup>The firstfruits of your grain, of your wine and of your oil, and the first fleece of your sheep, you shall give him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has chosen him out of all your tribes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5390E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5390E\"></sup>to stand and minister in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, him and his sons for all time.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“And if a Levite comes from any of your towns out of all Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5391F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5391F\"></sup>where he lives—and he may come when he desires—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5391G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5391G\"></sup>to the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will choose,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and ministers in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5392H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5392H\"></sup>like all his fellow Levites who stand to minister there before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>then he may have equal <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5393I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5393I\"></sup>portions to eat, besides what he receives from the sale of his patrimony.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“When you come into the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5394J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5394J\"></sup>you shall not learn to follow the abominable practices of those nations.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>There shall not be found among you anyone <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5395K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5395K\"></sup>who burns his son or his daughter as an offering, anyone who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5395L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5395L\"></sup>practices divination or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5395M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5395M\"></sup>tells fortunes or interprets omens, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5395N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5395N\"></sup>a sorcerer",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>or a charmer or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5396O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5396O\"></sup>a medium or a necromancer or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5396P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5396P\"></sup>one who inquires of the dead,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5397Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5397Q\"></sup>for whoever does these things is an abomination to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5397R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5397R\"></sup>because of these abominations the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is driving them out before you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You shall be blameless before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>for these nations, which you are about to dispossess, listen to fortune-tellers and to diviners. But as for you, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has not allowed you to do this.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5400S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5400S\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will raise up for you a prophet like me from among you, from your brothers—it is to him you shall listen—",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>just as you desired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God at Horeb <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5401T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5401T\"></sup>on the day of the assembly, when you said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5401U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5401U\"></sup>‘Let me not hear again the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God or see this great fire any more, lest I die.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5402V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5402V\"></sup>‘They are right in what they have spoken.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5403W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5403W\"></sup>I will raise up for them a prophet like you from among their brothers. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5403X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5403X\"></sup>And I will put my words in his mouth, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5403Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5403Y\"></sup>he shall speak to them all that I command him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5404Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5404Z\"></sup>And whoever will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5404AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5404AA\"></sup>not listen to my words that he shall speak in my name, I myself will require it of him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5405AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5405AB\"></sup>But the prophet who presumes to speak a word in my name that I have not commanded him to speak, or who speaks in the name of other gods, that same prophet shall die.’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And if you say in your heart, ‘How may we know the word that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not spoken?’—",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5407AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5407AC\"></sup>when a prophet speaks in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, if the word does not come to pass or come true, that is a word that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not spoken; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5407AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5407AD\"></sup>the prophet has spoken it presumptuously. You need not be afraid of him."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>“When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5408A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5408A\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God cuts off the nations whose land the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you, and you dispossess them and dwell in their cities and in their houses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5409B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5409B\"></sup>you shall set apart three cities for yourselves in the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you to possess.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall measure the distances and divide into three parts the area of the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you as a possession, so that any manslayer can flee to them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“This is the provision for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5411C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5411C\"></sup>the manslayer, who by fleeing there may save his life. If anyone kills his neighbor unintentionally without having hated him in the past—",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>as when someone goes into the forest with his neighbor to cut wood, and his hand swings the axe to cut down a tree, and the head slips from the handle and strikes his neighbor so that he dies—he may flee to one of these cities and live,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>lest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5413D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5413D\"></sup>the avenger of blood in hot anger pursue the manslayer and overtake him, because the way is long, and strike him fatally, though the man did not deserve to die, since he had not hated his neighbor in the past.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Therefore I command you, You shall set apart three cities.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5415E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5415E\"></sup>And if the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God enlarges your territory, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5415F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5415F\"></sup>as he has sworn to your fathers, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5415G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5415G\"></sup>gives you all the land that he promised to give to your fathers—",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>provided you are careful to keep all this commandment, which I command you today, by loving the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and by walking ever in his ways—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5416H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5416H\"></sup>then you shall add three other cities to these three,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>lest innocent blood be shed in your land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you for an inheritance, and so the guilt of bloodshed be upon you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“But if anyone hates his neighbor and lies in wait for him and attacks him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5418I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5418I\"></sup>and strikes him fatally so that he dies, and he flees into one of these cities,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>then the elders of his city shall send and take him from there, and hand him over to the avenger of blood, so that he may die.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5420J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5420J\"></sup>Your eye shall not pity him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5420K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5420K\"></sup>but you shall purge the guilt of innocent blood from Israel, so that it may be well with you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5421L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5421L\"></sup>“You shall not move your neighbor's landmark, which the men of old have set, in the inheritance that you will hold in the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you to possess.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“A single witness shall not suffice against a person for any crime or for any wrong in connection with any offense that he has committed. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5422M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5422M\"></sup>Only on the evidence of two witnesses or of three witnesses shall a charge be established.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>If <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5423N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5423N\"></sup>a malicious witness arises to accuse a person of wrongdoing,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>then both parties to the dispute shall appear before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5424O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5424O\"></sup>before the priests and the judges who are in office in those days.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The judges shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5425P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5425P\"></sup>inquire diligently, and if the witness is a false witness and has accused his brother falsely,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5426Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5426Q\"></sup>then you shall do to him as he had meant to do to his brother. So you shall purge the evil from your midst.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the rest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5427R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5427R\"></sup>shall hear and fear, and shall never again commit any such evil among you.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5428S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5428S\"></sup>Your eye shall not pity. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5428T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5428T\"></sup>It shall be life for life, eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>“When you go out to war against your enemies, and see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5429A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5429A\"></sup>horses and chariots and an army larger than your own, you shall not be afraid of them, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5429B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5429B\"></sup>with you, who brought you up out of the land of Egypt.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And when you draw near to the battle, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5430C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5430C\"></sup>the priest shall come forward and speak to the people",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and shall say to them, ‘Hear, O Israel, today you are drawing near for battle against your enemies: let not your heart faint. Do not fear or panic or be in dread of them,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is he who goes with you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5432D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5432D\"></sup>to fight for you against your enemies, to give you the victory.’",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the officers shall speak to the people, saying, ‘Is there any man who has built a new house and has not dedicated it? Let him go back to his house, lest he die in the battle and another man dedicate it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And is there any man who has planted a vineyard and has not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5434E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5434E\"></sup>enjoyed its fruit? Let him go back to his house, lest he die in the battle and another man enjoy its fruit.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5435F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5435F\"></sup>And is there any man who has betrothed a wife and has not taken her? Let him go back to his house, lest he die in the battle and another man take her.’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the officers shall speak further to the people, and say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5436G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5436G\"></sup>‘Is there any man who is fearful and fainthearted? Let him go back to his house, lest he make the heart of his fellows melt like his own.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And when the officers have finished speaking to the people, then commanders shall be appointed at the head of the people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“When you draw near to a city to fight against it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5438H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5438H\"></sup>offer terms of peace to it.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And if it responds to you peaceably and it opens to you, then all the people who are found in it shall do forced labor for you and shall serve you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But if it makes no peace with you, but makes war against you, then you shall besiege it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives it into your hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5441I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5441I\"></sup>you shall put all its males to the sword,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5442J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5442J\"></sup>but the women and the little ones, the livestock, and everything else in the city, all its spoil, you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5442K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5442K\"></sup>shall take as plunder for yourselves. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5442L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5442L\"></sup>you shall enjoy the spoil of your enemies, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Thus you shall do to all the cities that are very far from you, which are not cities of the nations here.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5444M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5444M\"></sup>in the cities of these peoples that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you for an inheritance, you shall save alive nothing that breathes,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5445N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5445N\"></sup>you shall devote them to complete destruction, the Hittites and the Amorites, the Canaanites and the Perizzites, the Hivites and the Jebusites, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has commanded,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5446O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5446O\"></sup>they may not teach you to do according to all their abominable practices that they have done for their gods, and so you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5446P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5446P\"></sup>sin against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“When you besiege a city for a long time, making war against it in order to take it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5447Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5447Q\"></sup>you shall not destroy its trees by wielding an axe against them. You may eat from them, but you shall not cut them down. Are the trees in the field human, that they should be besieged by you?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Only the trees that you know are not trees for food you may destroy and cut down, that you may build siegeworks against the city that makes war with you, until it falls."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>“If in the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you to possess someone is found slain, lying in the open country, and it is not known who killed him,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>then your elders and your judges shall come out, and they shall measure the distance to the surrounding cities.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And the elders of the city that is nearest to the slain man shall take a heifer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5451A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5451A\"></sup>that has never been worked and that has not pulled in a yoke.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the elders of that city shall bring the heifer down to a valley with running water, which is neither plowed nor sown, and shall break the heifer's neck there in the valley.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the priests, the sons of Levi, shall come forward, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has chosen <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5453B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5453B\"></sup>them to minister to him and to bless in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5453C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5453C\"></sup>by their word every dispute and every assault shall be settled.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And all the elders of that city nearest to the slain man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5454D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5454D\"></sup>shall wash their hands over the heifer whose neck was broken in the valley,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and they shall testify, ‘Our hands did not shed this blood, nor did our eyes see it shed.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Accept atonement, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for your people Israel, whom you have redeemed, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5456E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5456E\"></sup>do not set the guilt of innocent blood in the midst of your people Israel, so that their blood guilt be atoned for.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5457F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5457F\"></sup>you shall purge the guilt of innocent blood from your midst, when you do what is right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“When you go out to war against your enemies, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives them into your hand and you take them captive,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and you see among the captives a beautiful woman, and you desire to take her to be your wife,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and you bring her home to your house, she shall shave her head and pare her nails.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And she shall take off the clothes in which she was captured and shall remain in your house and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5461G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5461G\"></sup>lament her father and her mother a full month. After that you may go in to her and be her husband, and she shall be your wife.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But if you no longer delight in her, you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5462H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5462H\"></sup>let her go where she wants. But you shall not sell her for money, nor shall you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5462I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5462I\"></sup>treat her as a slave, since you have humiliated her.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“If a man has two wives, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5463J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5463J\"></sup>the one loved and the other unloved, and both the loved and the unloved have borne him children, and if the firstborn son belongs to the unloved,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>then on the day when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5464K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5464K\"></sup>he assigns his possessions as an inheritance to his sons, he may not treat the son of the loved as the firstborn in preference to the son of the unloved, who is the firstborn,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>but he shall acknowledge the firstborn, the son of the unloved, by giving him a double portion of all that he has, for he is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5465L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5465L\"></sup>the firstfruits of his strength. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5465M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5465M\"></sup>The right of the firstborn is his.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“If a man has a stubborn and rebellious son who will not obey the voice of his father or the voice of his mother, and, though they discipline him, will not listen to them,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>then his father and his mother shall take hold of him and bring him out to the elders of his city at the gate of the place where he lives,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and they shall say to the elders of his city, ‘This our son is stubborn and rebellious; he will not obey our voice; he is a glutton and a drunkard.’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5469N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5469N\"></sup>Then all the men of the city shall stone him to death with stones. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5469O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5469O\"></sup>So you shall purge the evil from your midst, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5469P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5469P\"></sup>and all Israel shall hear, and fear.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“And if a man has committed a crime punishable by death and he is put to death, and you hang him on a tree,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5471Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5471Q\"></sup>his body shall not remain all night on the tree, but you shall bury him the same day, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5471R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5471R\"></sup>a hanged man is cursed by God. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5471S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5471S\"></sup>You shall not defile your land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you for an inheritance."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>“You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5472A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5472A\"></sup>shall not see your brother's ox or his sheep going astray and ignore them. You shall take them back to your brother.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And if he does not live near you and you do not know who he is, you shall bring it home to your house, and it shall stay with you until your brother seeks it. Then you shall restore it to him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And you shall do the same with his donkey or with his garment, or with any lost thing of your brother's, which he loses and you find; you may not ignore it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5475B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5475B\"></sup>You shall not see your brother's donkey or his ox fallen down by the way and ignore them. You shall help him to lift them up again.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“A woman shall not wear a man's garment, nor shall a man put on a woman's cloak, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5476C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5476C\"></sup>for whoever does these things is an abomination to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“If you come across a bird's nest in any tree or on the ground, with young ones or eggs and the mother sitting on the young or on the eggs, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5477D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5477D\"></sup>you shall not take the mother with the young.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You shall let the mother go, but the young you may take for yourself, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5478E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5478E\"></sup>that it may go well with you, and that you may live long.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“When you build a new house, you shall make a parapet for your roof, that you may not bring the guilt of blood upon your house, if anyone should fall from it.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5480F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5480F\"></sup>“You shall not sow your vineyard with two kinds of seed, lest the whole yield be forfeited, the crop that you have sown and the yield of the vineyard.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall not plow with an ox and a donkey together.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You shall not wear cloth of wool and linen mixed together.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5483G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5483G\"></sup>“You shall make yourself tassels on the four corners of the garment with which you cover yourself.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“If any man takes a wife and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5484H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5484H\"></sup>goes in to her and then hates her",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and accuses her of misconduct and brings a bad name upon her, saying, ‘I took this woman, and when I came near her, I did not find in her evidence of virginity,’",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>then the father of the young woman and her mother shall take and bring out the evidence of her virginity to the elders of the city in the gate.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the father of the young woman shall say to the elders, ‘I gave my daughter to this man to marry, and he hates her;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and behold, he has accused her of misconduct, saying, “I did not find in your daughter evidence of virginity.” And yet this is the evidence of my daughter's virginity.’ And they shall spread the cloak before the elders of the city.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the elders of that city shall take the man and whip him,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and they shall fine him a hundred shekels of silver and give them to the father of the young woman, because he has brought a bad name upon a virgin of Israel. And she shall be his wife. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5490I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5490I\"></sup>He may not divorce her all his days.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But if the thing is true, that evidence of virginity was not found in the young woman,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>then they shall bring out the young woman to the door of her father's house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5492J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5492J\"></sup>the men of her city shall stone her to death with stones, because she has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5492K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5492K\"></sup>done an outrageous thing in Israel by whoring in her father's house. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5492L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5492L\"></sup>So you shall purge the evil from your midst.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5493M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5493M\"></sup>“If a man is found lying with the wife of another man, both of them shall die, the man who lay with the woman, and the woman. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5493N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5493N\"></sup>So you shall purge the evil from Israel.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“If there is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5494O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5494O\"></sup>betrothed virgin, and a man meets her in the city and lies with her,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>then you shall bring them both out to the gate of that city, and you shall stone them to death with stones, the young woman because she did not cry for help though she was in the city, and the man because he violated his neighbor's wife. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5495P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5495P\"></sup>So you shall purge the evil from your midst.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“But if in the open country a man meets a young woman who is betrothed, and the man seizes her and lies with her, then only the man who lay with her shall die.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But you shall do nothing to the young woman; she has committed no offense punishable by death. For this case is like that of a man attacking and murdering his neighbor,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>because he met her in the open country, and though the betrothed young woman cried for help there was no one to rescue her.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5499Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5499Q\"></sup>“If a man meets a virgin who is not betrothed, and seizes her and lies with her, and they are found,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>then the man who lay with her shall give to the father of the young woman fifty shekels of silver, and she shall be his wife, because he has violated her. He may not divorce her all his days.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5501R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5501R\"></sup>“A man shall not take his father's wife, so that he does not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5501S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5501S\"></sup>uncover his father's nakedness."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>“No one whose testicles are crushed or whose male organ is cut off shall enter the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5503A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5503A\"></sup>“No one born of a forbidden union may enter the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Even to the tenth generation, none of his descendants may enter the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5504B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5504B\"></sup>“No Ammonite or Moabite may enter the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Even to the tenth generation, none of them may enter the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forever,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5505C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5505C\"></sup>because they did not meet you with bread and with water on the way, when you came out of Egypt, and because they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5505D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5505D\"></sup>hired against you Balaam the son of Beor from Pethor of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5505E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5505E\"></sup>Mesopotamia, to curse you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God would not listen to Balaam; instead the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God turned <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5506F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5506F\"></sup>the curse into a blessing for you, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God loved you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5507G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5507G\"></sup>shall not seek their peace or their prosperity all your days forever.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“You shall not abhor an Edomite, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5508H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5508H\"></sup>he is your brother. You shall not abhor an Egyptian, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5508I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5508I\"></sup>you were a sojourner in his land.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Children born to them in the third generation may enter the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“When you are encamped against your enemies, then you shall keep yourself from every evil thing.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“If any man among you becomes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5511J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5511J\"></sup>unclean because of a nocturnal emission, then he shall go outside the camp. He shall not come inside the camp,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>but when evening comes, he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5512K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5512K\"></sup>bathe himself in water, and as the sun sets, he may come inside the camp.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“You shall have a place outside the camp, and you shall go out to it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And you shall have a trowel with your tools, and when you sit down outside, you shall dig a hole with it and turn back and cover up your excrement.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5515L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5515L\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God walks in the midst of your camp, to deliver you and to give up your enemies before you, therefore your camp must be holy, so that he may not see anything indecent among you and turn away from you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5516M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5516M\"></sup>“You shall not give up to his master a slave who has escaped from his master to you.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He shall dwell with you, in your midst, in the place that he shall choose within one of your towns, wherever it suits him. You shall not wrong him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“None of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5518N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5518N\"></sup>daughters of Israel shall be a cult prostitute, and none <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5518O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5518O\"></sup>of the sons of Israel shall be a cult prostitute.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You shall not bring the fee of a prostitute or the wages of a dog into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in payment for any vow, for both of these are an abomination to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5520P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5520P\"></sup>“You shall not charge interest on loans to your brother, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5520Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5520Q\"></sup>interest on money, interest on food, interest on anything that is lent for interest.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5521R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5521R\"></sup>You may charge a foreigner interest, but you may not charge your brother interest, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5521S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5521S\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God may bless you in all that you undertake in the land that you are entering to take possession of it.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5522T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5522T\"></sup>“If you make a vow to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, you shall not delay fulfilling it, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will surely require it of you, and you will be guilty of sin.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But if you refrain from vowing, you will not be guilty of sin.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>You shall be careful to do what has passed your lips, for you have voluntarily vowed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God what you have promised with your mouth.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“If you go into your neighbor's vineyard, you may eat your fill of grapes, as many as you wish, but you shall not put any in your bag.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>If you go into your neighbor's standing grain, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5526U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5526U\"></sup>you may pluck the ears with your hand, but you shall not put a sickle to your neighbor's standing grain."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>“When a man takes a wife and marries her, if then she finds no favor in his eyes because he has found some indecency in her, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5527A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5527A\"></sup>he writes her a certificate of divorce and puts it in her hand and sends her out of his house, and she departs out of his house,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and if she goes and becomes another man's wife,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and the latter man hates her and writes her a certificate of divorce and puts it in her hand and sends her out of his house, or if the latter man dies, who took her to be his wife,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5530B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5530B\"></sup>her former husband, who sent her away, may not take her again to be his wife, after she has been defiled, for that is an abomination before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And you shall not bring sin upon the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you for an inheritance.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5531C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5531C\"></sup>“When a man is newly married, he shall not go out with the army or be liable for any other public duty. He shall be free at home one year <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5531D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5531D\"></sup>to be happy with his wife whom he has taken.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“No one shall take a mill or an upper millstone in pledge, for that would be taking a life in pledge.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5533E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5533E\"></sup>“If a man is found stealing one of his brothers of the people of Israel, and if he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5533F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5533F\"></sup>treats him as a slave or sells him, then that thief shall die. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5533G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5533G\"></sup>So you shall purge the evil from your midst.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Take care, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5534H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5534H\"></sup>a case of leprous disease, to be very careful to do according to all that the Levitical priests shall direct you. As I commanded them, so you shall be careful to do.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Remember what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God did to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5535I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5535I\"></sup>Miriam <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5535J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5535J\"></sup>on the way as you came out of Egypt.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“When you make your neighbor a loan of any sort, you shall not go into his house to collect his pledge.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You shall stand outside, and the man to whom you make the loan shall bring the pledge out to you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And if he is a poor man, you shall not sleep in his pledge.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5539K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5539K\"></sup>You shall restore to him the pledge as the sun sets, that he may sleep in his cloak and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5539L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5539L\"></sup>bless you. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5539M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5539M\"></sup>it shall be righteousness for you before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“You shall not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5540N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5540N\"></sup>oppress a hired worker who is poor and needy, whether he is one of your brothers or one of the sojourners who are in your land within your towns.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5541O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5541O\"></sup>You shall give him his wages on the same day, before the sun sets (for he is poor and counts on it), <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5541P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5541P\"></sup>lest he cry against you to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and you be guilty of sin.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5542Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5542Q\"></sup>“Fathers shall not be put to death because of their children, nor shall children be put to death because of their fathers. Each one shall be put to death for his own sin.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5543R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5543R\"></sup>“You shall not pervert the justice due to the sojourner or to the fatherless, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5543S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5543S\"></sup>or take a widow's garment in pledge,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5544T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5544T\"></sup>you shall remember that you were a slave in Egypt and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God redeemed you from there; therefore I command you to do this.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5545U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5545U\"></sup>“When you reap your harvest in your field and forget a sheaf in the field, you shall not go back to get it. It shall be for the sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5545V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5545V\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God may bless you in all the work of your hands.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When you beat your olive trees, you shall not go over them again. It shall be for the sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When you gather the grapes of your vineyard, you shall not strip it afterward. It shall be for the sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5548W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5548W\"></sup>You shall remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt; therefore I command you to do this."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>“If there is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5549A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5549A\"></sup>dispute between men and they come into court and the judges decide between them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5549B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5549B\"></sup>acquitting the innocent and condemning the guilty,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>then if the guilty man deserves to be beaten, the judge shall cause him to lie down and be beaten in his presence with a number of stripes in proportion to his offense.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5551C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5551C\"></sup>Forty stripes may be given him, but not more, lest, if one should go on to beat him with more stripes than these, your brother be degraded in your sight.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5552D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5552D\"></sup>“You shall not muzzle an ox when it is treading out the grain.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5553E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5553E\"></sup>“If brothers dwell together, and one of them dies and has no son, the wife of the dead man shall not be married outside the family to a stranger. Her <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5553F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5553F\"></sup>husband's brother shall go in to her and take her as his wife and perform the duty of a husband's brother to her.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the first son whom she bears shall succeed to the name of his dead brother, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5554G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5554G\"></sup>his name may not be blotted out of Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And if the man does not wish to take his brother's wife, then his brother's wife shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5555H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5555H\"></sup>go up to the gate to the elders and say, ‘My husband's brother refuses to perpetuate his brother's name in Israel; he will not perform the duty of a husband's brother to me.’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the elders of his city shall call him and speak to him, and if he persists, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5556I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5556I\"></sup>‘I do not wish to take her,’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>then his brother's wife shall go up to him in the presence of the elders and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5557J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5557J\"></sup>pull his sandal off his foot and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5557K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5557K\"></sup>spit in his face. And she shall answer and say, ‘So shall it be done to the man who does not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5557L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5557L\"></sup>build up his brother's house.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the name of his house shall be called in Israel, ‘The house of him who had his sandal pulled off.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“When men fight with one another and the wife of the one draws near to rescue her husband from the hand of him who is beating him and puts out her hand and seizes him by the private parts,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>then you shall cut off her hand. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5560M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5560M\"></sup>Your eye shall have no pity.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5561N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5561N\"></sup>shall not have in your bag two kinds of weights, a large and a small.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You shall not have in your house two kinds of measures, a large and a small.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>A full and fair weight you shall have, a full and fair measure you shall have, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5563O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5563O\"></sup>that your days may be long in the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5564P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5564P\"></sup>all who do such things, all who act dishonestly, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5564Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5564Q\"></sup>are an abomination to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5565R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5565R\"></sup>“Remember what Amalek did to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5565S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5565S\"></sup>on the way as you came out of Egypt,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>how he attacked you on the way when you were faint and weary, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5566T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5566T\"></sup>cut off your tail, those who were lagging behind you, and he did not fear God.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5567U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5567U\"></sup>when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given you rest from all your enemies around you, in the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you for an inheritance to possess, you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5567V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5567V\"></sup>blot out the memory of Amalek from under heaven; you shall not forget."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>“When you come into the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you for an inheritance and have taken possession of it and live in it,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5569A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5569A\"></sup>you shall take some of the first of all the fruit of the ground, which you harvest from your land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you, and you shall put it in a basket, and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5569B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5569B\"></sup>go to the place that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will choose, to make his name to dwell there.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And you shall go to the priest who is in office at that time and say to him, ‘I declare today to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God that I have come into the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5570C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5570C\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to our fathers to give us.’",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the priest shall take the basket from your hand and set it down before the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“And you shall make response before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, ‘A <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5572D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5572D\"></sup>wandering Aramean was my father. And he went down into Egypt and sojourned there, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5572E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5572E\"></sup>few in number, and there he became a nation, great, mighty, and populous.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5573F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5573F\"></sup>the Egyptians treated us harshly and humiliated us and laid on us hard labor.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5574G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5574G\"></sup>we cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of our fathers, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard our voice and saw our affliction, our toil, and our oppression.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5575H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5575H\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought us out of Egypt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5575I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5575I\"></sup>with a mighty hand and an outstretched arm, with great deeds of terror, with signs and wonders.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And he brought us into this place and gave us this land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5576J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5576J\"></sup>a land flowing with milk and honey.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And behold, now I bring the first of the fruit of the ground, which you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, have given me.’ And you shall set it down before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and worship before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5578K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5578K\"></sup>you shall rejoice in all the good that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given to you and to your house, you, and the Levite, and the sojourner who is among you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“When you have finished paying all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5579L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5579L\"></sup>the tithe of your produce in the third year, which is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5579M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5579M\"></sup>the year of tithing, giving it to the Levite, the sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow, so that they may eat within your towns and be filled,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>then you shall say before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, ‘I have removed the sacred portion out of my house, and moreover, I have given it to the Levite, the sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow, according to all your commandment that you have commanded me. I have not transgressed any of your commandments, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5580N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5580N\"></sup>nor have I forgotten them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5581O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5581O\"></sup>I have not eaten of the tithe while I was mourning, or removed any of it while I was unclean, or offered any of it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5581P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5581P\"></sup>to the dead. I have obeyed the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God. I have done according to all that you have commanded me.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5582Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5582Q\"></sup>Look down from your holy habitation, from heaven, and bless your people Israel and the ground that you have given us, as you swore to our fathers, a land flowing with milk and honey.’",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“This day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God commands you to do these statutes and rules. You shall therefore be careful to do them with all your heart and with all your soul.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5584R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5584R\"></sup>You have declared today that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is your God, and that you will walk in his ways, and keep his statutes and his commandments and his rules, and will obey his voice.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has declared today that you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5585S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5585S\"></sup>a people for his treasured possession, as he has promised you, and that you are to keep all his commandments,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and that he will set you in praise and in fame and in honor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5586T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5586T\"></sup>high above all nations <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5586U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5586U\"></sup>that he has made, and that you shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5586V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5586V\"></sup>a people holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, as he promised.”"
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>Now Moses and the elders of Israel commanded the people, saying, “Keep the whole commandment that I command you today.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And on the day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5588A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5588A\"></sup>you cross over the Jordan to the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you, you shall set up large stones and plaster them with plaster.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5589B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5589B\"></sup>And you shall write on them all the words of this law, when you cross over to enter the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5589C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5589C\"></sup>a land flowing with milk and honey, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, has promised you.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And when you have crossed over the Jordan, you shall set up these stones, concerning which I command you today, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5590D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5590D\"></sup>on Mount Ebal, and you shall plaster them with plaster.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And there you shall build an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, an altar of stones. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5591E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5591E\"></sup>You shall wield no iron tool on them;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>you shall build an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God of uncut stones. And you shall offer burnt offerings on it to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and you shall sacrifice peace offerings and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5593F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5593F\"></sup>shall eat there, and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5593G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5593G\"></sup>shall rejoice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5594H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5594H\"></sup>you shall write on the stones all the words of this law very plainly.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Moses and the Levitical priests said to all Israel, “Keep silence and hear, O Israel: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5595I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5595I\"></sup>this day you have become the people of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall therefore obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, keeping his commandments and his statutes, which I command you today.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>That day Moses charged the people, saying,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“When you have crossed over the Jordan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5598J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5598J\"></sup>these shall stand on Mount Gerizim to bless the people: Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Joseph, and Benjamin.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And these shall stand on Mount Ebal for the curse: Reuben, Gad, Asher, Zebulun, Dan, and Naphtali.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5600K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5600K\"></sup>the Levites shall declare to all the men of Israel in a loud voice:",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5601L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5601L\"></sup>“‘Cursed be the man who makes a carved or cast metal image, an abomination to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, a thing made by the hands of a craftsman, and sets it up in secret.’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5601M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5601M\"></sup>And all the people shall answer and say, ‘Amen.’",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5602N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5602N\"></sup>“‘Cursed be anyone who dishonors his father or his mother.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5603O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5603O\"></sup>“‘Cursed be anyone who moves his neighbor's landmark.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5604P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5604P\"></sup>“‘Cursed be anyone who misleads a blind man on the road.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5605Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5605Q\"></sup>“‘Cursed be anyone who perverts the justice due to the sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5606R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5606R\"></sup>“‘Cursed be anyone who lies with his father's wife, because he has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5606S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5606S\"></sup>uncovered his father's nakedness.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5607T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5607T\"></sup>“‘Cursed be anyone who lies with any kind of animal.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5608U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5608U\"></sup>“‘Cursed be anyone who lies with his sister, whether the daughter of his father or the daughter of his mother.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5609V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5609V\"></sup>“‘Cursed be anyone who lies with his mother-in-law.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5610W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5610W\"></sup>“‘Cursed be anyone who strikes down his neighbor in secret.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5611X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5611X\"></sup>“‘Cursed be anyone who takes a bribe to shed innocent blood.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5612Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5612Y\"></sup>“‘Cursed be anyone who does not confirm the words of this law by doing them.’ And all the people shall say, ‘Amen.’"
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>“And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5613A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5613A\"></sup>if you faithfully obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, being careful to do all his commandments that I command you today, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will set you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5613B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5613B\"></sup>high above all the nations of the earth.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And all these blessings shall come upon you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5614C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5614C\"></sup>overtake you, if you obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Blessed shall you be in the city, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5615D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5615D\"></sup>blessed shall you be in the field.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Blessed shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5616E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5616E\"></sup>the fruit of your womb and the fruit of your ground and the fruit of your cattle, the increase of your herds and the young of your flock.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Blessed shall be your basket and your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5617F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5617F\"></sup>kneading bowl.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Blessed shall you be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5618G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5618G\"></sup>when you come in, and blessed shall you be when you go out.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5619H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5619H\"></sup>will cause your enemies who rise against you to be defeated before you. They shall come out against you one way and flee before you seven ways.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5620I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5620I\"></sup>will command the blessing on you in your barns and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5620J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5620J\"></sup>in all that you undertake. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5620K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5620K\"></sup>And he will bless you in the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5621L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5621L\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will establish you as a people holy to himself, as he has sworn to you, if you keep the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and walk in his ways.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5622M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5622M\"></sup>all the peoples of the earth shall see that you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5622N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5622N\"></sup>called by the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5622O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5622O\"></sup>afraid of you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5623P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5623P\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will make you abound in prosperity, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5623Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5623Q\"></sup>the fruit of your womb and in the fruit of your livestock and in the fruit of your ground, within the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to your fathers to give you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will open to you his good treasury, the heavens, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5624R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5624R\"></sup>to give the rain to your land in its season and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5624S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5624S\"></sup>to bless all the work of your hands. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5624T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5624T\"></sup>you shall lend to many nations, but you shall not borrow.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will make you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5625U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5625U\"></sup>the head and not the tail, and you shall only go up and not down, if you obey the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, which I command you today, being careful to do them,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5626V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5626V\"></sup>and if you do not turn aside from any of the words that I command you today, to the right hand or to the left, to go after other gods to serve them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5627W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5627W\"></sup>if you will not obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God or be careful to do all his commandments and his statutes that I command you today, then all these curses shall come upon you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5627X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5627X\"></sup>overtake you.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Cursed shall you be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5628Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5628Y\"></sup>in the city, and cursed shall you be in the field.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Cursed shall be your basket and your kneading bowl.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Cursed shall be the fruit of your womb and the fruit of your ground, the increase of your herds and the young of your flock.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Cursed shall you be when you come in, and cursed shall you be when you go out.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5632Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5632Z\"></sup>will send on you curses, confusion, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5632AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5632AA\"></sup>frustration in all that you undertake to do, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5632AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5632AB\"></sup>until you are destroyed and perish quickly on account of the evil of your deeds, because you have forsaken me.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5633AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5633AC\"></sup>the pestilence stick to you until he has consumed you off the land that you are entering to take possession of it.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5634AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5634AD\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will strike you with wasting disease and with fever, inflammation and fiery heat, and with drought and with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5634AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5634AE\"></sup>blight and with mildew. They shall pursue you until you perish.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5635AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5635AF\"></sup>the heavens over your head shall be bronze, and the earth under you shall be iron.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will make the rain of your land powder. From heaven dust shall come down on you until you are destroyed.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5637AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5637AG\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will cause you to be defeated before your enemies. You shall go out one way against them and flee seven ways before them. And you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5637AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5637AH\"></sup>shall be a horror to all the kingdoms of the earth.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5638AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5638AI\"></sup>your dead body shall be food for all birds of the air and for the beasts of the earth, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5638AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5638AJ\"></sup>there shall be no one to frighten them away.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will strike you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5639AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5639AK\"></sup>with the boils of Egypt, and with tumors and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5639AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5639AL\"></sup>scabs and itch, of which you cannot be healed.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will strike you with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5640AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5640AM\"></sup>madness and blindness and confusion of mind,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5641AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5641AN\"></sup>grope at noonday, as the blind grope in darkness, and you shall not prosper in your ways. And you shall be only oppressed and robbed continually, and there shall be no one to help you.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5642AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5642AO\"></sup>You shall betroth a wife, but another man shall ravish her. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5642AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5642AP\"></sup>You shall build a house, but you shall not dwell in it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5642AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5642AQ\"></sup>You shall plant a vineyard, but you shall not enjoy its fruit.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Your ox shall be slaughtered before your eyes, but you shall not eat any of it. Your donkey shall be seized before your face, but shall not be restored to you. Your sheep shall be given to your enemies, but there shall be no one to help you.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5644AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5644AR\"></sup>Your sons and your daughters shall be given to another people, while your eyes look on and fail with longing for them all day long, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5644AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5644AS\"></sup>but you shall be helpless.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>A nation that you have not known shall eat up the fruit of your ground and of all your labors, and you shall be only oppressed and crushed continually,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>so that you are driven mad <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5646AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5646AT\"></sup>by the sights that your eyes see.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will strike you on the knees and on the legs <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5647AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5647AU\"></sup>with grievous boils of which you cannot be healed, from the sole of your foot to the crown of your head.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5648AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5648AV\"></sup>bring you and your king whom you set over you to a nation that neither you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5648AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5648AW\"></sup>nor your fathers have known. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5648AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5648AX\"></sup>there you shall serve other gods of wood and stone.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And you shall become <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5649AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5649AY\"></sup>a horror, a proverb, and a byword among all the peoples where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will lead you away.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5650AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5650AZ\"></sup>You shall carry much seed into the field and shall gather in little, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5650BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5650BA\"></sup>the locust shall consume it.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5651BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5651BB\"></sup>You shall plant vineyards and dress them, but you shall neither drink of the wine nor gather the grapes, for the worm shall eat them.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>You shall have olive trees throughout all your territory, but you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5652BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5652BC\"></sup>shall not anoint yourself with the oil, for your olives shall drop off.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>You shall father sons and daughters, but they shall not be yours, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5653BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5653BD\"></sup>they shall go into captivity.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5654BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5654BE\"></sup>The cricket shall possess all your trees and the fruit of your ground.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5655BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5655BF\"></sup>The sojourner who is among you shall rise higher and higher above you, and you shall come down lower and lower.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5656BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5656BG\"></sup>He shall lend to you, and you shall not lend to him. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5656BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5656BH\"></sup>He shall be the head, and you shall be the tail.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5657BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5657BI\"></sup>“All these curses shall come upon you and pursue you and overtake you till you are destroyed, because you did not obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, to keep his commandments and his statutes that he commanded you.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>They shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5658BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5658BJ\"></sup>a sign and a wonder against you and your offspring forever.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5659BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5659BK\"></sup>Because you did not serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with joyfulness and gladness of heart, because of the abundance of all things,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>therefore you shall serve your enemies whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will send against you, in hunger and thirst, in nakedness, and lacking everything. And he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5660BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5660BL\"></sup>will put a yoke of iron on your neck until he has destroyed you.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5661BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5661BM\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will bring a nation against you from far away, from the end of the earth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5661BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5661BN\"></sup>swooping down like the eagle, a nation <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5661BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5661BO\"></sup>whose language you do not understand,",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>a hard-faced nation <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5662BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5662BP\"></sup>who shall not respect the old or show mercy to the young.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>It shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5663BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5663BQ\"></sup>eat the offspring of your cattle and the fruit of your ground, until you are destroyed; it also shall not leave you grain, wine, or oil, the increase of your herds or the young of your flock, until they have caused you to perish.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>“They shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5664BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5664BR\"></sup>besiege you in all your towns, until your high and fortified walls, in which you trusted, come down throughout all your land. And they shall besiege you in all your towns throughout all your land, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given you.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5665BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5665BS\"></sup>you shall eat the fruit of your womb, the flesh of your sons and daughters, whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5665BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5665BT\"></sup>in the siege and in the distress with which your enemies shall distress you.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>The man who is the most tender and refined among you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5666BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5666BU\"></sup>begrudge food to his brother, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5666BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5666BV\"></sup>the wife he embraces, and to the last of the children whom he has left,",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>so that he will not give to any of them any of the flesh of his children whom he is eating, because he has nothing else left, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5667BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5667BW\"></sup>in the siege and in the distress with which your enemy shall distress you in all your towns.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5668BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5668BX\"></sup>The most tender and refined woman among you, who would not venture to set the sole of her foot on the ground because she is so delicate and tender, will begrudge to the husband she embraces, to her son and to her daughter,",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>her afterbirth that comes out from between her feet and her children whom she bears, because lacking everything she will eat them secretly, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5669BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5669BY\"></sup>in the siege and in the distress with which your enemy shall distress you in your towns.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>“If you are not careful to do all the words of this law that are written in this book, that you may fear this glorious and awesome name, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5670BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5670BZ\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God,",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will bring on you and your offspring extraordinary afflictions, afflictions severe and lasting, and sicknesses grievous and lasting.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>And he will bring upon you again all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5672CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5672CA\"></sup>the diseases of Egypt, of which you were afraid, and they shall cling to you.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>Every sickness also and every affliction that is not recorded in the book of this law, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will bring upon you, until you are destroyed.",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>Whereas <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5674CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5674CB\"></sup>you were as numerous <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5674CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5674CC\"></sup>as the stars of heaven, you shall be left few in number, because you did not obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>And as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5675CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5675CD\"></sup>took delight in doing you good and multiplying you, so the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5675CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5675CE\"></sup>take delight in bringing ruin upon you and destroying you. And you shall be plucked off the land that you are entering to take possession of it.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>“And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5676CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5676CF\"></sup>will scatter you among all peoples, from one end of the earth to the other, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5676CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5676CG\"></sup>there you shall serve other gods <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5676CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5676CH\"></sup>of wood and stone, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5676CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5676CI\"></sup>which neither you nor your fathers have known.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5677CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5677CJ\"></sup>among these nations you shall find no respite, and there shall be no resting place for the sole of your foot, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5677CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5677CK\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give you there a trembling heart and failing eyes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5677CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5677CL\"></sup>a languishing soul.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>Your life shall hang in doubt before you. Night and day you shall be in dread and have no assurance of your life.",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5679CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5679CM\"></sup>In the morning you shall say, ‘If only it were evening!’ and at evening you shall say, ‘If only it were morning!’ because of the dread that your heart shall feel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5679CN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CN&quot;&gt;CN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5679CN\"></sup>the sights that your eyes shall see.",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5680CO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CO&quot;&gt;CO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5680CO\"></sup>will bring you back in ships to Egypt, a journey that I promised that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5680CP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CP&quot;&gt;CP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5680CP\"></sup>you should never make again; and there you shall offer yourselves for sale to your enemies as male and female slaves, but there will be no buyer.”"
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span> These are the words of the covenant that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses to make with the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5681A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5681A\"></sup>in the land of Moab, besides <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5681B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5681B\"></sup>the covenant that he had made with them at Horeb.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup> And Moses summoned all Israel and said to them: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5682C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5682C\"></sup>“You have seen all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did before your eyes in the land of Egypt, to Pharaoh and to all his servants and to all his land,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>the great <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5683D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5683D\"></sup>trials that your eyes saw, the signs, and those great wonders.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But to this day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5684E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5684E\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not given you a heart to understand or eyes to see or ears to hear.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5685F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5685F\"></sup>I have led you forty years in the wilderness. Your clothes have not worn out on you, and your sandals have not worn off your feet.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5686G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5686G\"></sup>You have not eaten bread, and you have not drunk wine or strong drink, that you may know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And when you came to this place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5687H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5687H\"></sup>Sihon the king of Heshbon and Og the king of Bashan came out against us to battle, but we defeated them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>We took their land and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5688I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5688I\"></sup>gave it for an inheritance to the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of the Manassites.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5689J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5689J\"></sup>Therefore keep the words of this covenant and do them, that you may prosper in all that you do.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“You are standing today, all of you, before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God: the heads of your tribes, your elders, and your officers, all the men of Israel,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>your little ones, your wives, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5691K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5691K\"></sup>sojourner who is in your camp, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5691L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5691L\"></sup>the one who chops your wood to the one who draws your water,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>so that you may enter into the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5692M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5692M\"></sup>sworn covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is making with you today,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>that he may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5693N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5693N\"></sup>establish you today as his people, and that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5693O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5693O\"></sup>he may be your God, as he promised you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5693P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5693P\"></sup>as he swore to your fathers, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>It is not with you alone <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5694Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5694Q\"></sup>that I am making this sworn covenant,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>but with whoever is standing here with us today before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5695R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5695R\"></sup>and with whoever is not here with us today.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“You know how we lived in the land of Egypt, and how we came through the midst of the nations through which you passed.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And you have seen their detestable things, their idols of wood and stone, of silver and gold, which were among them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Beware lest there be among you a man or woman or clan or tribe whose heart is turning away today from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God to go and serve the gods of those nations. Beware lest there be among you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5698S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5698S\"></sup>a root bearing poisonous and bitter fruit,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>one who, when he hears the words of this sworn covenant, blesses himself in his heart, saying, ‘I shall be safe, though I walk in the stubbornness of my heart.’ This will lead to the sweeping away of moist and dry alike.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will not be willing to forgive him, but rather <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5700T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5700T\"></sup>the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5700U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5700U\"></sup>his jealousy will smoke against that man, and the curses written in this book will settle upon him, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5700V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5700V\"></sup>will blot out his name from under heaven.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will single him out from all the tribes of Israel for calamity, in accordance with all the curses of the covenant written in this Book of the Law.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And the next generation, your children who rise up after you, and the foreigner who comes from a far land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5702W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5702W\"></sup>will say, when they see the afflictions of that land and the sicknesses with which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has made it sick—",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>the whole land burned out with brimstone and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5703X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5703X\"></sup>salt, nothing sown and nothing growing, where no plant can sprout, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5703Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5703Y\"></sup>an overthrow like that of Sodom and Gomorrah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5703Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5703Z\"></sup>Admah, and Zeboiim, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> overthrew in his anger and wrath—",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>all the nations <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5704AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5704AA\"></sup>will say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5704AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5704AB\"></sup>‘Why has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> done thus to this land? What caused the heat of this great anger?’",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then people will say, ‘It is because they abandoned the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers, which he made with them when he brought them out of the land of Egypt,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and went and served other gods and worshiped them, gods whom they had not known and whom he had not allotted to them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Therefore the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was kindled against this land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5707AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5707AC\"></sup>bringing upon it all the curses written in this book,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5708AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5708AD\"></sup>uprooted them from their land in anger and fury and great wrath, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5708AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5708AE\"></sup>cast them into another land, as they are this day.’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“The secret things belong to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, but the things that are revealed belong to us and to our children forever, that we may do all the words of this law."
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">30 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5710A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5710A\"></sup>“And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5710B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5710B\"></sup>when all these things come upon you, the blessing and the curse, which I have set before you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5710C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5710C\"></sup>you call them to mind among all the nations where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has driven you,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5711D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5711D\"></sup>return to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, you and your children, and obey his voice in all that I command you today, with all your heart and with all your soul,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5712E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5712E\"></sup>will restore your fortunes and have mercy on you, and he will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5712F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5712F\"></sup>gather you again from all the peoples where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has scattered you.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5713G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5713G\"></sup>If your outcasts are in the uttermost parts of heaven, from there the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will gather you, and from there he will take you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will bring you into the land that your fathers possessed, that you may possess it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5714H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5714H\"></sup>And he will make you more prosperous and numerous than your fathers.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5715I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5715I\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will circumcise your heart and the heart of your offspring, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5715J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5715J\"></sup>so that you will love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with all your heart and with all your soul, that you may live.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will put all these curses on your foes and enemies who persecuted you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And you shall again obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and keep all his commandments that I command you today.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5718K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5718K\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will make you abundantly prosperous in all the work of your hand, in the fruit of your womb and in the fruit of your cattle and in the fruit of your ground. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5718L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5718L\"></sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will again take delight in prospering you, as he took delight in your fathers,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>when you obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, to keep his commandments and his statutes that are written in this Book of the Law, when you turn to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with all your heart and with all your soul.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“For this commandment that I command you today <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5720M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5720M\"></sup>is not too hard for you, neither is it far off.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5721N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5721N\"></sup>It is not in heaven, that you should say, ‘Who will ascend to heaven for us and bring it to us, that we may hear it and do it?’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Neither is it beyond the sea, that you should say, ‘Who will go over the sea for us and bring it to us, that we may hear it and do it?’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But the word is very near you. It is in your mouth and in your heart, so that you can do it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“See, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5724O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5724O\"></sup>I have set before you today life and good, death and evil.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>If you obey the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God that I command you today, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5725P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5725P\"></sup>by loving the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, by walking in his ways, and by keeping his commandments and his statutes and his rules, then you shall live and multiply, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will bless you in the land that you are entering to take possession of it.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But if <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5726Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5726Q\"></sup>your heart turns away, and you will not hear, but are drawn away to worship other gods and serve them,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5727R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5727R\"></sup>I declare to you today, that you shall surely perish. You shall not live long in the land that you are going over the Jordan to enter and possess.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I call heaven and earth to witness against you today, that I have set before you life and death, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5728S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5728S\"></sup>blessing and curse. Therefore choose life, that you and your offspring may live,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>loving the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, obeying his voice <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5729T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5729T\"></sup>and holding fast to him, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5729U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5729U\"></sup>he is your life and length of days, that you may dwell in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5729V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5729V\"></sup>the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swore to your fathers, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, to give them.”"
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">31 </span>So Moses continued to speak these words to all Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he said to them, “I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5731A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5731A\"></sup>120 years old today. I am no longer able to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5731B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5731B\"></sup>go out and come in. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has said to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5731C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5731C\"></sup>‘You shall not go over this Jordan.’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5732D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5732D\"></sup>himself will go over before you. He will destroy these nations before you, so that you shall dispossess them, and Joshua will go over at your head, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5732E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5732E\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5733F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5733F\"></sup>as he did to Sihon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5733G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5733G\"></sup>and Og, the kings of the Amorites, and to their land, when he destroyed them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give them over to you, and you shall do to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5734H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5734H\"></sup>according to the whole commandment that I have commanded you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5735I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5735I\"></sup>Be strong and courageous. Do not fear or be in dread of them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5735J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5735J\"></sup>for it is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God who goes with you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5735K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5735K\"></sup>He will not leave you or forsake you.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5736L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5736L\"></sup>Moses summoned Joshua and said to him in the sight of all Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5736M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5736M\"></sup>“Be strong and courageous, for you shall go with this people into the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sworn to their fathers to give them, and you shall put them in possession of it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>It is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5737N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5737N\"></sup>who goes before you. He will be with you; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5737O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5737O\"></sup>he will not leave you or forsake you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5737P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5737P\"></sup>Do not fear or be dismayed.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5738Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5738Q\"></sup>wrote this law and gave it to the priests, the sons of Levi, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5738R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5738R\"></sup>who carried the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and to all the elders of Israel.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Moses commanded them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5739S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5739S\"></sup>“At the end of every seven years, at the set time in the year of release, at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5739T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5739T\"></sup>the Feast of Booths,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>when all Israel comes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5740U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5740U\"></sup>to appear before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God at the place that he will choose, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5740V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5740V\"></sup>you shall read this law before all Israel in their hearing.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5741W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5741W\"></sup>Assemble the people, men, women, and little ones, and the sojourner within your towns, that they may hear and learn to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and be careful to do all the words of this law,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and that their children, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5742X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5742X\"></sup>who have not known it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5742Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5742Y\"></sup>may hear and learn to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5742Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5742Z\"></sup>as long as you live in the land that you are going over the Jordan to possess.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5743AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5743AA\"></sup>“Behold, the days approach when you must die. Call Joshua and present yourselves in the tent of meeting, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5743AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5743AB\"></sup>I may commission him.” And Moses and Joshua went and presented themselves in the tent of meeting.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5744AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5744AC\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared in the tent in a pillar of cloud. And the pillar of cloud stood over the entrance of the tent.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5745AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5745AD\"></sup>“Behold, you are about to lie down with your fathers. Then this people will rise and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5745AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5745AE\"></sup>whore after the foreign gods among them in the land that they are entering, and they will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5745AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5745AF\"></sup>forsake me and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5745AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5745AG\"></sup>break my covenant that I have made with them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then my anger will be kindled against them in that day, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5746AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5746AH\"></sup>I will forsake them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5746AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5746AI\"></sup>hide my face from them, and they will be devoured. And many evils and troubles will come upon them, so that they will say in that day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5746AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5746AJ\"></sup>‘Have not these evils come upon us because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5746AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5746AK\"></sup>our God is not among us?’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And I will surely hide my face in that day because of all the evil that they have done, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5747AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5747AL\"></sup>they have turned to other gods.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Now therefore write <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5748AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5748AM\"></sup>this song and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5748AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5748AN\"></sup>teach it to the people of Israel. Put it in their mouths, that this song may be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5748AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5748AO\"></sup>a witness for me against the people of Israel.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>For when I have brought them into the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5749AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5749AP\"></sup>flowing with milk and honey, which I swore to give to their fathers, and they have eaten and are full and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5749AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5749AQ\"></sup>grown fat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5749AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5749AR\"></sup>they will turn to other gods and serve them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5749AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5749AS\"></sup>despise me and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5749AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5749AT\"></sup>break my covenant.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And when many evils and troubles have come upon them, this song shall confront them as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5750AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5750AU\"></sup>a witness (for it will live unforgotten in the mouths of their offspring). For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5750AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5750AV\"></sup>I know what they are inclined to do even today, before I have brought them into the land that I swore to give.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So Moses wrote this song the same day and taught it to the people of Israel.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5752AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5752AW\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commissioned Joshua the son of Nun and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5752AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5752AX\"></sup>“Be strong and courageous, for you shall bring the people of Israel into the land that I swore to give them. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5752AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5752AY\"></sup>I will be with you.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When Moses had finished <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5753AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5753AZ\"></sup>writing the words of this law in a book to the very end,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Moses commanded <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5754BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5754BA\"></sup>the Levites who carried the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“Take this Book of the Law <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5755BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5755BB\"></sup>and put it by the side of the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, that it may be there for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5755BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5755BC\"></sup>a witness against you.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>For I know how rebellious and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5756BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5756BD\"></sup>stubborn you are. Behold, even today while I am yet alive with you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5756BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5756BE\"></sup>you have been rebellious against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. How much more after my death!",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Assemble to me all the elders of your tribes and your officers, that I may speak <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5757BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5757BF\"></sup>these words in their ears and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5757BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5757BG\"></sup>call heaven and earth to witness against them.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>For I know that after my death <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5758BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5758BH\"></sup>you will surely act corruptly and turn aside from the way that I have commanded you. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5758BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5758BI\"></sup>in the days to come <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5758BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5758BJ\"></sup>evil will befall you, because you will do what is evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5758BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5758BK\"></sup>provoking him to anger through the work of your hands.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Moses spoke the words of this song until they were finished, in the ears of all the assembly of Israel:"
		},
		"32": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">32 </span>“Give ear, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5760A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5760A\"></sup>O heavens, and I will speak,and let <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5760B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5760B\"></sup>the earth hear the words of my mouth.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>May <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5761C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5761C\"></sup>my teaching drop as the rain,my speech distill as the dew,like gentle rain upon the tender grass,and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5761D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5761D\"></sup>like showers upon the herb.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For I will proclaim the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;ascribe <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5762E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5762E\"></sup>greatness to our God!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5763F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5763F\"></sup>“The Rock, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5763G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5763G\"></sup>his work is perfect,for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5763H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5763H\"></sup>all his ways are justice.A God of faithfulness and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5763I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5763I\"></sup>without iniquity,just and upright is he.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They have dealt corruptly with him;they are no longer his children <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5764J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5764J\"></sup>because they are blemished;they are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5764K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5764K\"></sup>a crooked and twisted generation.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Do you thus repay the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,you foolish and senseless people?Is not he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5765L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5765L\"></sup>your father, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5765M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5765M\"></sup>created you,who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5765N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5765N\"></sup>made you and established you?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5766O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5766O\"></sup>Remember the days of old;consider the years of many generations;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5766P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5766P\"></sup>ask your father, and he will show you,your elders, and they will tell you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When the Most High <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5767Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5767Q\"></sup>gave to the nations their inheritance,when he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5767R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5767R\"></sup>divided mankind,he fixed the borders of the peoplesaccording to the number of the sons of God.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s portion is his people,Jacob his allotted heritage.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“He found him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5769S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5769S\"></sup>in a desert land,and in the howling waste of the wilderness;he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5769T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5769T\"></sup>encircled him, he cared for him,he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5769U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5769U\"></sup>kept him as the apple of his eye.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5770V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5770V\"></sup>Like an eagle that stirs up its nest,that flutters over its young,spreading out its wings, catching them,bearing them on its pinions,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5771W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5771W\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> alone guided him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5771X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5771X\"></sup>no foreign god was with him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5772Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5772Y\"></sup>He made him ride on the high places of the land,and he ate the produce of the field,and he suckled him with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5772Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5772Z\"></sup>honey out of the rock,and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5772AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5772AA\"></sup>oil out of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5772AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5772AB\"></sup>the flinty rock.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Curds from the herd, and milk from the flock,with fat of lambs,rams of Bashan and goats,with the very finest of the wheat—and you drank foaming wine made from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5773AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5773AC\"></sup>the blood of the grape.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5774AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5774AD\"></sup>Jeshurun grew fat, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5774AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5774AE\"></sup>kicked;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5774AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5774AF\"></sup>you grew fat, stout, and sleek;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5774AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5774AG\"></sup>then he forsook God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5774AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5774AH\"></sup>who made himand scoffed at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5774AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5774AI\"></sup>the Rock of his salvation.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5775AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5775AJ\"></sup>They stirred him to jealousy with strange gods;with abominations they provoked him to anger.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5776AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5776AK\"></sup>They sacrificed to demons that were no gods,to gods they had never known,to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5776AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5776AL\"></sup>new gods that had come recently,whom your fathers had never dreaded.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You were unmindful of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5777AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5777AM\"></sup>the Rock that bore you,and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5777AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5777AN\"></sup>forgot the God who gave you birth.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5778AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5778AO\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw it and spurned them,because of the provocation of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5778AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5778AP\"></sup>his sons and his daughters.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5779AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5779AQ\"></sup>‘I will hide my face from them;I will see what their end will be,for they are a perverse generation,children in whom is no faithfulness.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5780AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5780AR\"></sup>They have made me jealous with what is no god;they have provoked me to anger <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5780AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5780AS\"></sup>with their idols.So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5780AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5780AT\"></sup>I will make them jealous with those who are no people;I will provoke them to anger with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5780AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5780AU\"></sup>a foolish nation.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5781AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5781AV\"></sup>a fire is kindled by my anger,and it burns to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5781AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5781AW\"></sup>the depths of Sheol,devours the earth and its increase,and sets on fire the foundations of the mountains.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“‘And I will heap disasters upon them;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5782AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5782AX\"></sup>I will spend my arrows on them;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>they shall be wasted with hunger,and devoured by plagueand poisonous pestilence;I will send <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5783AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5783AY\"></sup>the teeth of beasts against them,with the venom of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5783AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5783AZ\"></sup>things that crawl in the dust.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5784BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5784BA\"></sup>Outdoors the sword shall bereave,and indoors terror,for young man and woman alike,the nursing child with the man of gray hairs.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5785BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5785BB\"></sup>I would have said, “I will cut them to pieces;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5785BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5785BC\"></sup>I will wipe them from human memory,”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>had I not feared provocation by the enemy,lest their adversaries should misunderstand,lest they should say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5786BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5786BD\"></sup>“Our hand is triumphant,it was not the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who did all this.”’",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“For they are a nation void of counsel,and there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5787BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5787BE\"></sup>no understanding in them.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5788BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5788BF\"></sup>If they were wise, they would understand this;they would <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5788BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5788BG\"></sup>discern their latter end!",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>How could <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5789BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5789BH\"></sup>one have chased a thousand,and two have put ten thousand to flight,unless their Rock <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5789BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5789BI\"></sup>had sold them,and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given them up?",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5790BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5790BJ\"></sup>their rock is not as our Rock;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5790BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5790BK\"></sup>our enemies are by themselves.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>For their vine <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5791BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5791BL\"></sup>comes from the vine of Sodomand from the fields of Gomorrah;their grapes are grapes of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5791BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5791BM\"></sup>poison;their clusters are bitter;",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>their wine is the poison of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5792BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5792BN\"></sup>serpentsand the cruel venom of asps.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“‘Is not this laid up in store with me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5793BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5793BO\"></sup>sealed up in my treasuries?",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5794BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5794BP\"></sup>Vengeance is mine, and recompense,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5794BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5794BQ\"></sup>for the time when their foot shall slip;for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5794BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5794BR\"></sup>the day of their calamity is at hand,and their doom comes swiftly.’",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5795BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5795BS\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will vindicate his people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5795BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5795BT\"></sup>and have compassion on his servants,when he sees that their power is goneand there is none remaining, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5795BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5795BU\"></sup>bond or free.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then he will say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5796BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5796BV\"></sup>‘Where are their gods,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5796BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5796BW\"></sup>the rock in which they took refuge,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>who ate the fat of their sacrificesand drank the wine of their drink offering?Let them rise up and help you;let them be your protection!",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“‘See now that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5798BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5798BX\"></sup>I, even I, am he,and there is no god beside me;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5798BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5798BY\"></sup>I kill and I make alive;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5798BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5798BZ\"></sup>I wound and I heal;and there is none that can deliver out of my hand.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5799CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5799CA\"></sup>I lift up my hand to heavenand swear, As I live forever,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>if I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5800CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5800CB\"></sup>sharpen my flashing swordand my hand takes hold on judgment,I will take vengeance on my adversariesand will repay those who hate me.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>I will make my arrows drunk with blood,and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5801CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5801CC\"></sup>my sword shall devour flesh—with the blood of the slain and the captives,from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5801CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5801CD\"></sup>long-haired heads of the enemy.’",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5802CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5802CE\"></sup>“Rejoice with him, O heavens;bow down to him, all gods,for he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5802CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5802CF\"></sup>avenges the blood of his childrenand takes vengeance on his adversaries.He repays those who hate himand cleanses his people's land.”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Moses came and recited all the words of this song in the hearing of the people, he and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5803CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5803CG\"></sup>Joshua the son of Nun.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>And when Moses had finished speaking all these words to all Israel,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>he said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5805CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5805CH\"></sup>“Take to heart all the words by which I am warning you today, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5805CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5805CI\"></sup>that you may command them to your children, that they may be careful to do all the words of this law.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>For it is no empty word for you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5806CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5806CJ\"></sup>but your very life, and by this word you shall live long in the land that you are going over the Jordan to possess.”",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>That very day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>“Go up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5808CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5808CK\"></sup>this mountain of the Abarim, Mount Nebo, which is in the land of Moab, opposite Jericho, and view the land of Canaan, which I am giving to the people of Israel for a possession.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>And die on the mountain which you go up, and be gathered to your people, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5809CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5809CL\"></sup>Aaron your brother died in Mount Hor and was gathered to his people,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5810CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5810CM\"></sup>because you broke faith with me in the midst of the people of Israel at the waters of Meribah-kadesh, in the wilderness of Zin, and because you did not treat me as holy in the midst of the people of Israel.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5811CN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CN&quot;&gt;CN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5811CN\"></sup>you shall see the land before you, but you shall not go there, into the land that I am giving to the people of Israel.”"
		},
		"33": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">33 </span>This is the blessing with which Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5812A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5812A\"></sup>the man of God blessed the people of Israel before his death.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5813B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5813B\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came from Sinaiand dawned from Seir upon us;he shone forth from Mount Paran;he came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5813C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5813C\"></sup>from the ten thousands of holy ones,with flaming fire at his right hand.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Yes, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5814D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5814D\"></sup>he loved his people,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5814E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5814E\"></sup>all his holy ones were in his hand;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5814F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5814F\"></sup>so they followed in your steps,receiving direction from you,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5815G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5815G\"></sup>Moses commanded us a law,as a possession for the assembly of Jacob.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Thus the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5816H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5816H\"></sup>became king in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5816I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5816I\"></sup>Jeshurun,when the heads of the people were gathered,all the tribes of Israel together.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5817J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5817J\"></sup>“Let Reuben live, and not die,but let his men be few.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And this he said of Judah:“Hear, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the voice of Judah,and bring him in to his people.With your hands contend for him,and be a help against his adversaries.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5819K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5819K\"></sup>of Levi he said,“Give to Levi <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5819L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5819L\"></sup>your Thummim,and your Urim to your godly one,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5819M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5819M\"></sup>whom you tested at Massah,with whom you quarreled at the waters of Meribah;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>who said of his father and mother,‘I regard them not’;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5820N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5820N\"></sup>he disowned his brothersand ignored his children.For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5820O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5820O\"></sup>they observed your wordand kept your covenant.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5821P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5821P\"></sup>They shall teach Jacob your rulesand Israel your law;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5821Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5821Q\"></sup>they shall put incense before youand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5821R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5821R\"></sup>whole burnt offerings on your altar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Bless, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, his substance,and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5822S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5822S\"></sup>accept the work of his hands;crush the loins of his adversaries,of those who hate him, that they rise not again.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5823T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5823T\"></sup>Of Benjamin he said,“The beloved of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> dwells in safety.The High God surrounds him all day long,and dwells between his shoulders.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5824U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5824U\"></sup>of Joseph he said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5824V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5824V\"></sup>“Blessed by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be his land,with the choicest gifts of heaven <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5824W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5824W\"></sup>above,and of the deep that crouches beneath,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>with the choicest fruits of the sunand the rich yield of the months,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>with the finest produce of the ancient mountainsand the abundance of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5826X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5826X\"></sup>the everlasting hills,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>with the best gifts of the earth and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5827Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5827Y\"></sup>its fullnessand the favor of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5827Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5827Z\"></sup>him who dwells in the bush.May these rest on the head of Joseph,on the pate of him who is prince among his brothers.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5828AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5828AA\"></sup>A firstborn bull—he has majesty,and his horns are the horns of a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5828AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5828AB\"></sup>wild ox;with them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5828AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5828AC\"></sup>he shall gore the peoples,all of them, to the ends of the earth;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5828AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5828AD\"></sup>they are the ten thousands of Ephraim,and they are the thousands of Manasseh.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And of Zebulun he said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5829AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5829AE\"></sup>“Rejoice, Zebulun, in your going out,and Issachar, in your tents.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They shall call peoples <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5830AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5830AF\"></sup>to their mountain;there they offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5830AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5830AG\"></sup>right sacrifices;for they draw from the abundance of the seasand the hidden treasures of the sand.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5831AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5831AH\"></sup>of Gad he said,“Blessed be he who enlarges Gad!Gad crouches <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5831AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5831AI\"></sup>like a lion;he tears off arm and scalp.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5832AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5832AJ\"></sup>He chose the best of the land for himself,for there a commander's portion was reserved;and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5832AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5832AK\"></sup>he came with the heads of the people,with Israel he executed the justice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and his judgments for Israel.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5833AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5833AL\"></sup>of Dan he said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5833AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5833AM\"></sup>“Dan is a lion's cub<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5833AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5833AN\"></sup>that leaps from Bashan.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5834AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5834AO\"></sup>of Naphtali he said,“O Naphtali, sated with favor,and full of the blessing of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5834AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5834AP\"></sup>possess the lake and the south.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5835AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5835AQ\"></sup>of Asher he said,“Most blessed of sons be Asher;let him be the favorite of his brothers,and let him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5835AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5835AR\"></sup>dip his foot in oil.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Your bars shall be iron and bronze,and as your days, so shall your strength be.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5837AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5837AS\"></sup>“There is none like God, O <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5837AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5837AT\"></sup>Jeshurun,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5837AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5837AU\"></sup>who rides through the heavens to your help,through the skies in his majesty.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The eternal God is your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5838AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5838AV\"></sup>dwelling place,and underneath are the everlasting arms.And he thrust out the enemy before youand said, ‘Destroy.’",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Israel lived in safety,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5839AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5839AW\"></sup>Jacob lived <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5839AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5839AX\"></sup>alone,in a land of grain and wine,whose heavens drop down dew.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Happy are you, O Israel! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5840AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5840AY\"></sup>Who is like you,a people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5840AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5840AZ\"></sup>saved by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5840BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5840BA\"></sup>the shield of your help,and the sword of your triumph!Your enemies shall come fawning to you,and you shall tread upon their backs.”"
		},
		"34": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">34 </span>Then Moses went up from the plains of Moab <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5841A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5841A\"></sup>to Mount Nebo, to the top of Pisgah, which is opposite Jericho. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> showed him all the land, Gilead as far as Dan,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>all Naphtali, the land of Ephraim and Manasseh, all the land of Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5842B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5842B\"></sup>as far as the western sea,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5843C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5843C\"></sup>the Negeb, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5843D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5843D\"></sup>the Plain, that is, the Valley of Jericho <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5843E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5843E\"></sup>the city of palm trees, as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5843F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5843F\"></sup>Zoar.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5844G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5844G\"></sup>“This is the land of which I swore to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, ‘I will give it to your offspring.’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5844H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5844H\"></sup>I have let you see it with your eyes, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5844I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5844I\"></sup>you shall not go over there.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> died there in the land of Moab, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and he buried him in the valley in the land of Moab opposite Beth-peor; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5846J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5846J\"></sup>no one knows the place of his burial to this day.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5847K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5847K\"></sup>Moses was 120 years old when he died. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5847L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5847L\"></sup>His eye was undimmed, and his vigor unabated.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5848M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5848M\"></sup>wept for Moses in the plains of Moab thirty days. Then the days of weeping and mourning for Moses were ended.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Joshua the son of Nun was full of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5849N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5849N\"></sup>the spirit of wisdom, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5849O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5849O\"></sup>Moses had laid his hands on him. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5849P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5849P\"></sup>the people of Israel obeyed him and did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And there has not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5850Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5850Q\"></sup>arisen a prophet since in Israel like Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5850R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5850R\"></sup>whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> knew face to face,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>none like him for all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5851S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5851S\"></sup>the signs and the wonders that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent him to do in the land of Egypt, to Pharaoh and to all his servants and to all his land,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and for all the mighty power and all the great deeds of terror that Moses did in the sight of all Israel."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;